title: quick tuna squares
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients until well mixed and smooth.
Pat mixture into well-greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Melt oleo in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg and milk together. Roll chicken in this mixture and then roll in dry mixture. Arrange in pan with melted oleo.
Turn over to coat both sides. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Turn over and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Mix rice and 1/2 the milk with salt and sugar.
Pour into a buttered baking dish. Bake 4 hours at 325°, stirring frequently and adding the rest of the milk.
When cool, top with cinnamon sugar.

title: nina's frozen salad
directions: Slowly whip buttermilk and pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add drained fruit. FREEZE.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll 1/4-inch thick. Cut out and fill with Raisin Filling.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and beaten egg.
Add to corn and mix thoroughly.
Add hot milk.
Pour into 1-quart baking pan.
Dot with butter and sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Set in pan of water and bake until custard is set.
Cook about 1 hour at 325°.

title: raisin brown bread
directions: Preheat oven to
Grease
a
x 5-inch pan.
In large bowl
stir
all
ingredients and 2 tablespoons hot water just until well combined.
Pour into loaf pan; bake 50 minutes or until bread
pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from pan and cool on wire
racks.
Good
served
with peanut butter or cream cheese.

title: pumpkin or potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into uncooked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 425° and cook for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: "dump it" chicken casserole
directions: "Dump" all ingredients in casserole.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs and fruit.
Pour into ungreased large cake pan.
Mix 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts. Sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter and mix in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken & yellow rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken breast with garlic, salt and pepper.
Then place in slightly greased frying pan and brown lightly (don't fry done).
Place chicken in large casserole dish and set aside.
IN pan where chicken was browned combine onion, bell peppers and saute until tender then add your broth and large can of stewed tomatoes, bay leaves and salt & pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over your chicken and sprinkle packages of rice evenly into the liquid.
Bake at 400 degrees about an hour or until chicken and rice appear to be done.
You may wish to add some water if not enough liquid to cook your rice properly.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients; add to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
For variety, add chopped nuts, chocolate chips or coconut.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
In large skillet, add beef and onions.
Fry until brown.
Add tomatoes and grated cheese; mix well.
Pour this into casserole over the cooked macaroni and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: stir fried pork and pasta
directions: Trim fat from pork and cut into 2 x 1 x 1/8-inch slices.
Toss with cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and pepper in a glass bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
Add ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer in a covered pan over low heat for 1 hour to all day.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together in large bowl. Add enough Slice to blend well.
Put in freezing can of an ice cream freezer.
Add the rest of the Slice up to fill line on can. Put top on and start freezing.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In bowl #1, mix together flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In bowl #2, cream together butter and sugar, then add eggs, zucchini, extract, milk and nuts.
Alternate wet and dry ingredients in large bowl.
Spread into loaf pans and bake 1 hour.
Let cool on racks.
These freeze great for gifts.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients and pour into greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
(Can be cooked in casserole in 350° oven for 1 hour.)

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix mushroom soup, tomatoes and milk in saucepan.
Heat and stir until well blended.
Dice 3/4 of cheese.
Layer beef, cheese, chips and milk mixture in long cake pan.
Heat in oven at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar; cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Be sure to mix
well.
When
cutting in shortening, the mixture should look like
coarse corn meal. Cover; let rise at least 2 hours.
Roll out
on
floured board using enough flour added to make it easy to
handle.
This may take extra
1/2 to 3/4 cup flour. Roll out
and
cut
desired size. Place on greased pan (use Pam).
Let rise until doubled in
size. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 4 dozen.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add Cool Whip. Layer graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers, pudding and graham crackers. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Is better if eaten next day.

title: spinach delicious
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and heat through.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: b.l.t. salad toss
directions: Combine celery, tomato, onion and dressing.
Toss lightly. Chill until serving time.
Cook bacon and crumble into mixture and spoon over lettuce.
Toss lightly.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole and bake 30 minutes, covered, in 350° oven.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Then cool 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Spoon out onto buttered wax paper.

title: mrs. taylor's oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat well the eggs, vanilla and soda. Mix thoroughly all dry ingredients. Make a hollow in mixture. Put in ground raisins. Pour over them the hot Crisco, stirring raisins as you pour. Mix all together; let stand 1 hour. Add beaten egg mixture. When well mixed, drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until brown on edges. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add water and chicken stock and heat to boiling, stirring until stock dissolves. Gradually add noodles and salt; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in precooked and drained broccoli.
Add garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes.
Reduce heat; add milk and cheese, stirring until melted.
Add pepper. Serves 6 to 8.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients except cornflake crumbs and butter, and pour into greased 9 x 13 casserole.
Top with cornflakes and butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be refrigerated overnight.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer at medium speed until butter has broken up.
Mold into pans.
Makes enough crust for 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans or equivalent.
Can be frozen or refrigerated.

title: quick jalapeno corn
directions: Drain corn.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour pimentos and peppers in dish.
Cut cream cheese into chunks and put in corn mixture. Stir.
Microwave 4 minutes and stir.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: breakfast scones
directions: Sift flour; add baking powder, salt, sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and sufficient water to make soft dough.
Turn on lightly floured board.
Pat into sheet 1-inch thick.
Cut into rounds or squares. Fold over double and brush with milk.
Place on oiled baking pan. Dust with sugar.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and garlic.
Brown meat.
Add everything except noodles.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In a large pan, layer noodles and then meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: chicken tucson
directions: Cook and cube chicken.
Combine next six ingredients in large bowl.
Add chicken.
Place a single layer of crushed Doritos on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer half of the chicken sauce mixture on top of the chips.
Layer half of the cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Mix in drained sausage and cheese.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish with bread and cover with mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mississippi rice
directions: Mix together in baking dish and cook for 40 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Roll into a ball.
Cut meat in small, thin strips.
Roll cheese ball into meat until covered. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: tomato zucchini casserole
directions: Layer the tomatoes, zucchini and onions.
Add salt, pepper and crushed basil.
Cover with breadcrumbs.
Sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Then add cheese.
Dot casserole with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then uncover for 45 minutes more.
This is an excellent side dish.

title: praline pecan crunch(dog food)
directions: Combine cereal and pecans in a 9x13 pan, set aside.
Combine corn syrup,
brown sugar and margarine in a microwaveable bowl and cook on high for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave for another 1/2 - 1 1/2 minutes more until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
pour over cereal mixture and mix until coated evenly.
Bake for one hour at 350 degrees, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet.
Break into pieces.

title: lynn's hamburger skillet dinner
directions: Cut up bacon and fry until crisp.
Add hamburger and chopped onion and brown.
Drain.
Add soy sauce and pepper.
Slice vegetables to add in layers.
Cover and cook on high heat for 1 minute.
Reduce heat and cook slowly for 15 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add cheese before serving so it melts.

title: surprise stuffing(vegetable casserole)
directions: In a large skillet, saute squash and onion in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Transfer to a greased one-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vinegar and food coloring; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Pour into (3) 9-inch pans, greased and floured.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes (or not); cut in bite-size pieces.
Combine flour, cheese, salt, pepper and paprika in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few times in bag, coating well.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in melted margarine and cover both sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until potatoes are soft and browned.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix together first four ingredients real good and chill until syrupy, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Whip cream real good.
Add whipped cream, nuts, pineapple and cheese to jello mixture.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: lemon butter
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
If not thick enough, add 1 tablespoon of cornstarch mixed in water and continue stirring until thick.
Refrigerate.
A good spread for toast, nut bread, etc.

title: hot potato-frank salad
directions: Peel and slice hot potatoes.
Add frankfurters, eggs, scallions and relish.
Combine Wish-Bone dressing, salt and mustard in small saucepan.
Heat, while stirring, until hot.
Pour over potato mixture, tossing gently.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Add pepper, corn and tomato juice.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Pour into long bread pan.
Mix cornbread as usual and drop over top of mixture.
Bake until bread is done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and put in two graham cracker pie crusts. Chill well before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: I use nacho chips instead of crackers.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 35 squares.

title: baked apple slices
directions: Peel and core apples into 4 sections; dampen apple slices in water or lemon juice (for a tangy treat).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar on both sides of apple.
Place apple in center of crescent roll and fold over.
Pull up sides of roll and pinch to seal.
Dab with butter.
Place on a cookie sheet in center of oven.
Bake in 350° oven for about 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in square baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour into dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
For more servings, use 2 cans of corn and double the rest of the ingredients.
Leave out salt.

title: weight watchers chili
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Exchanges: 2 protein and 1 vegetable.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with sour cream plus milk.
Add vanilla.
Spread 1/2 of cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients together.
Make a hole in the center of the dry ingredients.
Pour all the liquids in the hole and mix by hand.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cassie's cookie salad
directions: Add fruit and 1/2 package crushed Keebler's fudge stripe cookies and mix rest of ingredients.
Top with rest of crushed cookies.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and shape into small balls. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Mix last 5 ingredients together. Bring to a boil.
Add meatballs.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: steak carbonade
directions: Place steaks in flat glass baking pans and shake on layer of lemon pepper.
Press into steak.
Cover with beer (Pilsner) or for a heavier flavor, a dark beer;
just enough to cover steaks. Marinate for 3 or 4 hours.
Grill on outdoor grill to your taste. Do not salt until served.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt. Make hole in center of dry mixture.
Add bananas, pineapple, chopped nuts, coconut, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix by hand.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: fort knox fish fillets
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium-low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, nutmeg and mustard until smooth.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted; remove from heat.

title: clam chip dip
directions: Soften and crumble cream cheese.
Mix ingredients together. Chill for 15 minutes before serving.

title: savory spinach squares
directions: Cook spinach until just tender enough to chop.
Drain well, then chop.
Beat eggs; add milk and melted butter, spices and cheese.
Stir in cooked rice and drained spinach.
Bake in greased shallow 1-quart baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes until set, bubbly and golden.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: howard's dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine; press into pan and refrigerate while preparing other part of dessert.
Beat together 1 can condensed milk and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Mix condensed milk and lemon juice mixture with Cool Whip and coconut.
Mix gelatin with cut up strawberries and cinnamon.
Put 1/2 of condensed milk mixture on top of crumb crust, then add layer of strawberry gelatin mixture.
Top with remaining condensed milk mixture.
Garnish with coconut or cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.
Serves approximately 15 people.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk until smooth (2 minutes).
Fold in remaining ingredients except wafers.
Spread in layers.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9x13 baking dish.
Spread undrained pineapple over bottom of baking dish.
Add blueberries over pineapple.
Sprinkle 3/4 c. sugar over blueberries.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Top with generous amounts of pecans.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 c. sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
After 25 minutes, cut through cake mix in many places to permit juice to bubble through. Return to oven for remainder of cooking time.

title: steak san marco
directions: In large skillet, arrange meat.
Cover with onion soup mix and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic powder, pepper, oil and vinegar.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter, one-half cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and salt.
Add small amount at a time. Add buttermilk.
Cook in unbaked pie shell at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, or until pie is golden brown.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; mix in pineapple and lemon juice; pour into mold and refrigerate until partially set.	Then fold in pineapple, cheese and then whipping cream.	Refrigerate until firm; unmold and serve.

title: parve:  crazy cake and broiled crunchy icing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Make three holes in dry ingredients; in each hole, put one of the following:
2 tablespoons vinegar, 12 tablespoons oil and 2 tablespoons vanilla. Pour 2 cups of cold water over all.
Mix well by hand or mixer. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until done, when a toothpick is inserted into middle of cake.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Mix the ground beef with chopped mushrooms, milk, salt, chopped onion, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard. Spoon mixture over the steak.
Roll the sides of steak like jelly roll over the stuffing.
Bind with bacon strips, wrapped around the outside of the roll at regular intervals.
Fasten bacon ends with toothpicks.
Bacon strips should be close enough together that when it is sliced, each slice will be wrapped with a bacon strip.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
This is a great dish for entertaining.
It can be made a day ahead of time and put in the oven to bake just before guests arrive.
Two stuffed steaks can be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, margarine and eggs together.
Mix flour, salt, cinnamon and soda together.
Add mixtures together.
Mix 1/2 cup flour with dates, cherries, pineapples and pecans.
Add more flour if necessary to make stiff dough.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Top with piece of candied cherry or pecan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix butter and sugar first, then add in flour, eggs, vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips. Place batter in a 9 in deep dish pie crust and bake for 1 hour.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt the candy and 1 stick of butter and set aside.
Cream the sugar and 1 stick of butter.
Add eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda and baking powder.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to eggs and sugar mixture, alternating.
Add candy and pecans.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° in tube pan.

title: hearts of palm spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 9 inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers or melba rounds.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and brown.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and mustard in saucepan.
Add egg, then vinegar and water.
Cook until thickened.
Add bacon to cooked mixture.
Serve over dandelion or lettuce.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook tomatoes, onion, pepper and garlic in a 6 quart or larger pot 30 to 40 minutes until soft.
Puree in food processor or press through a food mill.
Return puree to pot and simmer until mixture is reduced by half--30 to 40 minutes.
Tie seasoning together in a cheesecloth bag and add to the tomato mixture.
Simmer, stirring frequently to avoid scorching and sticking until the catsup is very thick.
Remove spice bag.
Spoon into clean hot jars leaving 1/4-inch head space; seal.
Process in a boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Yield:
about 7 pints.

title: baskins-robbins pie
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top of mixture. Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Use a wooden spoon to stir and at least a 17 x 10 3/4 x 1-inch cookie sheet to turn brittle on.
The slower you cook it, the darker it gets.
When cold, break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: caramel filled chocolate cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Blend well.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture. Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of pecans.
Using a good teaspoon of dough, shape around 1 caramel candy, covering completely.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving 1/3 cup crumbs for topping. Place in a well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve promptly.

title: baking powder kolacky
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly. Chill overnight. Roll out dough. Cut in small circles.
Place a small amount of filling in center of each. Bake at 375° about 12 minutes or until done.
Use fillings of choice.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add combined cocoa and flour; beat well.
Add nut meats. Bake in 2 buttered 7 x 10 1/2-inch pans in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares or strips.
Store in covered container.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel and grind pears.
Cook until tender.
Add other ingredients and cook until mixture is thick.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: no bake peanut butter pie
directions: Beat confectioners sugar, cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and frozen whipped topping until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust and put in freezer until firm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, cream of mushroom soup and half of fried onion rings and put in casserole dish.
Top with remaining onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies(sugar free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool. Fold in apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: mexican biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt (or for you beginners just use 3 cups self-rising flour and leave out the other 3 ingredients).
Cut in oleo with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add sour cream, Cheddar cheese and peppers, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface, and knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 4-inch round cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: day before breakfast dish
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with bread cubes. Brown meat and drain.
Layer on top of bread.
Layer cheese. Beat eggs, salt and milk. Pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mesquite bean jelly
directions: One-half bushel mesquite beans at stage of maturity where there is a slight amount of red color on pods.
Wash and break them into small pieces; add 2 cups lemon juice and 3 to 4 quarts water and cook for 1 hour over low.
Take 5 cups of the mixture, place in large kettle and bring to a boil.
Add one box or one bottle of pectin jelling agent.
Stir in well and bring to a good boil.
Add 7 1/2 cups sugar and cook 5 minutes.
Pour into glasses.
Green or red food coloring may be added or the jelly may be left its natural color.

title: fried mallard
directions: Remove breast from ducks and chop into pieces.
Marinate in 1 quart milk for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove.
Mix together 1 cup fresh milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Dip duck into milk mixture and then roll in flour.
Preheat vegetable oil and fry at medium temperature until brown.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, spice and onion.
Stir well and saute for 15 minutes.
Simmer an additional 15 minutes.
While sauce is sauteing, cook the noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles; set aside.
Put 4 tablespoons sauce in bottom of long glass or metal pan.
Next, put 1 layer of 3 long noodles, then cottage cheese, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Keep layering until all ingredients are used up.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 14 to 16 people.

title: sunny punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water over heat.
Mix all ingredients.
I have substituted Equal for sugar and diet ginger ale and my family never knows the difference.
This is wonderful frozen to the slushy point!

title: mexican chicken stew
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove chicken and set aside. Add remaining ingredients, except onion to skillet; mix well. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked chicken and onion; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan chocolate drops
directions: Melt chocolate and paraffin over hot water.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil or waxed paper.
Allow to set.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan at 250° just until margarine melts and coats pan.
Mix sugar, flour and vanilla; mix well.
Add milk to mixture and stir until smooth.
Pour berries into milk mixture and then pour all into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Combine first 6 ingredients with salt and pepper to taste.
Fill pie pastry with mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Toss the cheese with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle on pie and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Remove and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.

title: crab dip(warm)
directions: Remove shells and pat dry.
Mix everything together with fork. Don't overmix so crabmeat doesn't break up too much.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle extra cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Keep warm while serving.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Melt your oleo in casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until good and bubbly. Add grated cheese on top and cook until melted.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook on medium heat until candy thermometer reads 300° (hard-crack stage), stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in oil and food coloring, keeping face away from mixture as aroma is very strong.
Immediately pour onto an oiled cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Sift powdered sugar into large mixing bowl.
Sift cocoa into powdered sugar.
Melt cheese and oleo in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; add powdered sugar and cocoa.
Stir until mixed.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Crumb ground beef in a casserole dish.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour over ground beef.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in chocolate.
Pour into well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from pan.
Place hot cake under tight fitting cake cover until cold.

title: hot and spicy shrimp dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts; dice.
Add shrimp, cream cheese, mayonnaise, picante sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with red peppers and green onion, if desired.
Serve with chips and assorted raw vegetables.
Makes 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: pineapple-orange salad
directions: Place pineapple with juice in saucepan and bring to a boil. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Stir in buttermilk and celery; set aside to cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm and serve.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese sauce for baked potatoes
directions: Saute celery and onion in 2 to 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Combine with remaining ingredients in crock-pot or saucepan.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve on baked potatoes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots just until tender; slice and drain.
Cut bell pepper in short strips.
Mix all vegetables together and set aside.

title: brownies
directions: Put in chocolate, flour, sugar and butter.
Cut it up.
Put it in this little block.
Put it in the oven on medium.
Cook 30 minutes.
Let it cool 10 minutes and give it to the people with milk.

title: variation for lunch
directions: Cook, drain and cut asparagus in 1-inch pieces.
Spread in 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cover
with
bread, 1 1/2 cups cheese and ham. Blend eggs,
milk
and
seasonings.
Pour
over
bread. Refrigerate 8 hours or
overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.
Last 15 minutes,
top
with
3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and finish baking.
Let stand
5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix oil, honey, eggs and milk in large bowl.
Stir in bran and raisins.
Let stand about 6 minutes.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt, mixing until well moistened.
Fill well oiled muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. Yields about 18 muffins.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ginger ale) together in a large container and add water to make one gallon. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Have ungreased cookie sheets ready. Process flour and pecans in a food processor or blender until nuts are very finely chopped.
Beat butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
With mixer on low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture just until blended. Roll level tablespoonfuls dough into balls.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on wire rack to cool completely, then roll in confectioners sugar again.
Store airtight up to 2 weeks or freeze.

title: kansas corn scallop
directions: Drain liquid from whole kernel corn into cup. Beat eggs slightly; stir in corn, 1/4 cup corn liquid, cream-style corn, evaporated milk, melted margarine, onion, salt and pepper. Fold in crackers and diced cheese. Bake in greased baking dish at 325° for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: almond cheese pine cone
directions: In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese, cheese spread and Blue cheese until smooth.
Stir in green onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and refrigerate about one hour. Shape cheese mixture to resemble a pine cone.
Beginning at narrow end of cone, press almonds about 1/4-inch deep into mixture in rows, extending each almond at a slight angle.
Overlap almonds until pine cone is covered.

title: clubhouse chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken on both sides in oil.
Stir in the tomatoes, mushrooms, water, Italian seasoning, and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 - 15 min. or until chicken juices run clear.
Remove chicken and keep warm. Combine the flour and cold water until smooth; stir into tomato mixture.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 min. or until thickened.
Serve chicken and sauce over rice.

title: squash creole
directions: Cook sliced squash in salted water until tender; drain.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Blend in flour.
Add chopped tomatoes, pepper, onion, salt and brown sugar.

title: ritz pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites with baking powder until medium stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until stiff.
Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Spread in a greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well; let stand 1/2 hour.
Chill.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Mix with other ingredients, except bananas and wafers.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
Pour over layered, sliced bananas and vanilla wafers.
Let cool before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Combine bananas, biscuit mix and nuts.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into bread loaf pan (no need to grease).
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until nicely browned.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: end of month stroganoff
directions: Saute hamburger in butter with onion and garlic.
When brown, add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and chicken soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: marty's salad creation
directions: Toss the first 4 ingredients together; place on salad plates. Top each serving with 1/4 of a golden Delicious apple (chopped), a few dried cherries or dried cranberries and sugared slivered almonds.
(Stir the slivered almonds and sugar over medium heat until golden.)

title: taco salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Bronw meat and first 6 ingredients.
Melt Velveeta, chili pepper and tomatoes in the top of double boiler.
Sprinkle meat mixture over lettuce and tomato.
Pour cheese mixture over this and then Fritos.
Mix/toss together.

title: salad supreme
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions and pour in 8 x 10-inch dish.
Allow to almost congeal and add crushed pineapple. Sprinkle chopped pecans over mix and return to refrigerator to completely congeal.

title: stir-fry with corned beef
directions: Layer as written in 12-inch skillet.
Cover and steam until tender, lifting and turning occasionally with spatula.
Heat (12 ounce) can Libby's corned beef and serve with veggies.
Add Worcestershire sauce, if desired.

title: harold's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Add water and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture and mix.
Stir in oats, nuts, raisins, chocolate chips and coconut.
Dough may be divided and various combinations of nuts, raisins, chips added.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: about 8 dozen.

title: fruitcake
directions: Mix eggs and water together. Add all other ingredients and mix by hand until moistened. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 80 to 90 minutes in 350° oven. Remove. Let set 15 minutes. Invert and remove from pan.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Combine well beaten eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Stir until flour is barely moist.

title: spice cake
directions: Add vinegar to milk to sour it.
Add soda to sour milk. Cream sugar
with shortening.
Add egg, sour milk and then dry ingredients.
Pour	in
an	8-inch	square greased pan and cut into bars.	This is a thin cake.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and arrange to cover a 12 x 15-inch pan. Beat egg and spread over crust.
Bake according to directions on package.
Pat crust to reduce puffiness.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing mix and spread over crust. Sprinkle with veggies and cheese.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: cherry winks
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
In second bowl, beat margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Stir in flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and chopped cherries.
Shape tablespoons of dough into balls and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place on greased cookie sheets and top with cherry quarters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: holiday punch
directions: Several hours ahead, mix together the fruit juices and water. Place in covered container in refrigerator to chill.
At serving time, combine mixture with chilled ginger ale and club soda. Makes 25 servings.

title: fresh rhubarb refrigerator cake
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice together.
Add rhubarb.
Line narrow, oblong pan or spring-form pan with waxed paper and fill with alternate layers of fruit mixture and ladyfingers.
Chill 6 hours or longer.

title: oreo snowballs
directions: Crush Oreo cookies to fine crumbs; use blender or food processor. Add softened cream cheese. Blend well. Shape into small balls. Dip into melted almond bark. Cool on waxed paper.

title: golden pineapple casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cube.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Place bread in 2-quart baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine pineapple, juice, sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until set and browned.
Serves 8.
Goes good with ham.

title: waldorf astoria chocolate cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cocoa and salt).
Mix separately water, margarine and vanilla, then add to dry mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, if using angel food cake pan, greased and bottom lined with waxed paper.
Let cool in pan right side up.

title: turtle cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cake according to package.
Stir in melted oleo.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan; bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean spinach and partially dry.
Add water chestnuts, bean sprouts, eggs, onion and crumbled bacon.
Combine sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste, salad oil and vinegar and shake well or put in blender.
Do not add dressing until just before serving.

title: herb crackers
directions: Mix dressing, dill and oil.
Toss crackers in mixture; drain on paper towels.
Store in tin can.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter, sugar, melted butter and cream cheese. Add Cool Whip and vanilla. Mix well with slow mixer. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill overnight.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion, dill weed and a dash of pepper in margarine until onion is tender.
Combine egg, bread crumbs, milk and onion mixture; add salmon.
Mix well.
Shape into a 6 x 3-inch oiled shallow loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.
Top with cheese sauce.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add the flour, salt and mace.
Add vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 60 to 80 minutes.
This pound cake freezes very well.

title: noodle beef bake
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Brown hamburger and onion. Season with salt and pepper. Mix noodles, hamburger and soups. Place in a 9 x 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta burgers
directions: Combine and mix well.
Make patties and brown on both sides. Pour condensed mushroom soup over meat; add kidney beans and green pepper.
Cook 10 minutes on low and add shredded cheese.
Cook for 5 minutes and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature and mix all ingredients except nuts. Mix well and roll into a ball. Roll the cheese ball in the chopped nuts and chill. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: no cook rocky road fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8-inch square pan with aluminum foil.
Combine cocoa and melted butter or margarine in a bowl; stir until smooth. Add salt and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar and milk, stirring until smooth.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Turn into pan. Cover and chill.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Chop nuts and set aside.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Sift together 4 times. Set aside.
Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs with mixer.
Add mashed bananas and mix well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and buttermilk, scraping bowl often.
Mix well.
Mix in nuts by hand.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix
oleo
and	sugars until sugar dissolves.
Add oatmeal, Special K, wheat germ, eggs and vanilla;
mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by very large tablespoons onto greased cookie sheets.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook sliced carrots (about 20 minutes), just until tender, not soft, and drain.
In a large bowl mix tomato soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Add carrots, green pepper rings and onion rings into liquid.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add vanilla and grated zucchini. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all together; add maraschino cherries for color and walnuts or pecans to taste.
Refrigerate several hours until serving.

title: jerome bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with whole graham crackers. Mix 1 1/2 sticks margarine, egg, sugar and evaporated milk and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour over layer. Place another layer of graham crackers on top.
Mix remaining margarine (softened), powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. Spread on top layer.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit and rice salad
directions: Cook rice.
Cool, then add the fruit cocktail, marshmallows, apples and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare yellow sheet cake.
Let cake cool completely. Prepare jello as directed.
Using a fork, press holes throughout entire cake.
Pour jello over cake, allowing jello to run into holes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown and drain meat; season according to directions on taco seasonings package.
Drain and dice potatoes and add to meat.
Drain peas and add to meat.
Put enchilada sauce in shallow bowl.
Dip six tortillas in sauce and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put half of meat mixture over tortillas and sprinkle one third of cheese on top.
Repeat layers.
Dip remaining six tortillas and cover casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and pour remaining sauce over casserole.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 45 minutes.

title: bean "lovers" dish
directions: Put beans, tomato paste and catsup in a baking dish.
Fry hamburger. Remove burger from fat.
Fry in fat the chopped onion and green pepper.
Mix together in baking dish with hamburger and bean mixture.
Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil chopped celery for 5 minutes, then drain.
Add soup, pepper, melted butter and pimiento.
Mix together and put in an 8-inch casserole dish.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
If you choose, instead of putting butter in celery mix, you can mix with cracker crumbs and spread on top of mix.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Blend for 1 minute in the blender.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with electric mixer on medium speed until well mixed.
If not well mixed, cornbread will be pasty.
Pour into greased iron skillet or casserole dish.
If iron skillet is used, heat batter filled skillet on top of range 3 or 4 minutes before baking.
This makes a very crispy crust.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Cream softened cream cheese and blend with grated Cheddar and other ingredients.
Roll into two balls.
Roll in pecans (crushed) and refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 60 to 65 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients into well.
Mix until smooth by hand.
Pour into 3 greased and floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: gnocchi
directions: In Mixmaster bowl; use dough hooks if possible.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and oil. Add salt, stirring to break up into fine pieces. Add the remaining ingredients. Cook for 30 minutes. Add chili powder to suit taste.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in 2 tablespoons of soy sauce for 30 minutes. Spray nonstick pan with Pam.
Brown garlic; add chicken and cook thoroughly.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Cook until onion is translucent.
Combine the other 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, water, cornstarch and red pepper.
Add to meat and vegetables.
Cook until liquid thickens.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: cashew hot dish
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 3 quart casserole dish.
Top with cashews and chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: french onion soup
directions: Preheat frying pan to 300°.
Slowly saute onions in melted margarine to a deep brown.
Add bouillon, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, very slowly at 225° for 1 hour.
Serve with toast cubes sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: savory sausage and peppers
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage in oil over medium heat. Remove with a slotted spoon and keep warm. In the drippings, saute peppers and onion until crisp tender. In a bowl combine water and contents of one soup mix envelope. Add soup mixture, hot pepper sauce and sausage to the vegetables. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until thickened. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and boil them together about 1 minute.
Add the beets from both cans but only add the liquid from one can.
Bring these ingredients to a boil and boil together for about 5 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
These should be made one or two day's prior to being served.

title: potato egg brunch cake
directions: Night Before:
fry bacon.
Drain, chop or crumble.
Place the frozen hash browns in refrigerator to thaw. Shred cheese.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix butter and boiling water together.
Let cool.
Mix flour, yeast, sugar and egg.
Add butter mixture.
Let rise in warm place.
Roll out and shape rolls.
Let rise again in warm place. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Brush melted butter on hot rolls.
Be sure to grease pan before rolling out and shaping rolls.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook carrots until not quite tender.
Set carrots and chicken aside.
In saucepan over medium heat melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add broth, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Lower heat and add shredded cheese until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in carrots, cooked chicken and pimentos. Spread in shallow 2-quart casserole dish (can also use oblong baking dish).

title: sweet sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet; drain.
Add pork and beans, brown sugar, mustard and ketchup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on burger buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: margaritas
directions: Freeze; shake or stir before serving.

title: scampi natua flambe
directions: Preheat pan with olive oil over high flame.
Add small amount of garlic; stir once.
Add shrimp and dash of salt and fresh ground pepper.
Sear on both sides until just white all the way through.
Remove to plate; drain on paper towel.
Add garlic, shallots, parsley and tomato.
Add 1 circle (3/4 ounce) brandy; flame and stir.
Slowly add white wine until flame is out.
Add 1 cup heavy cream, juice of 1/2 large lemon and bring to simmer. Reduce flame.
Add Hollandaise and scampi (important:
no water). Cook off.
Pour over fettucini.
Finish with paprika.

title: whistle pig(ground hog)
directions: Take a medium 4 foot pole.
Go into an old field, watch for a ground hot (whistle pig) to go into a log or his hole.
Take pole and twist into the groundhog's hair and pull him.
If you can't twist him out, go back to the house and get matches and old rags or wet leaves.
Place these in the end of the log or hole and light with a match to smoke him out.
If he gets away, go back to the house and get your gun.
Hide in the nearby weeds or old grapevine, wait until ground hog comes out, usually in the afternoon about 1 or evening about 6 o'clock.

title: savory beef stew
directions: Brown beef in oil in large skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, tapioca, broth, garlic, parsley, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring mixture to boil.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add onion.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce, oregano, salt and red and black pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole (macque choux)
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine.
Add corn and Ro-Tel; mix together (best if mixed the day before).

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Mix in the small Mix-N-Store.
Serve in the party server with raw vegetables.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Serve as dip for fresh fruit.
Arrange fresh fruit pieces on platter.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce. Boil egg noodles according to directions, rinse and drain.
Add mushrooms, cream of chicken soup, cream of broccoli soup or cream of mushroom and shredded Velveeta cheese or any Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of broccoli soup or cream of mushroom

title: orange julius
directions: Pour all ingredients into a blender.
Blend together.
Add more orange juice, if desired.
Pour and drink.

title: peanut butter yummies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls; roll each in peanuts.
Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: About 2 1/2 dozen.

title: out of this world lime salad
directions: Combine jello and marshmallows.
Add boiling water.
Stir until marshmallows are partly melted.
Add pineapple.
Mix well; refrigerate until partially set.
Remove and stir in nuts, cottage cheese and cherries.
Fold in stiffly whipped cream or prepared topping.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: play doh
directions: Put dry ingredients in a pan.
Add 1 cup water (add food coloring to water) and 1 tablespoon cooking oil.
Mix.
Cook a few minutes.
Cook on high, stirring constantly, until forms a ball.

title: mexican veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well in 9 x 13 dish and top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions; drain.
Steam the broccoli until tender but still crunchy; cool.
In a large bowl combine pasta and broccoli with all the remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add crabmeat and vegetables.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook for 1 minute; serve immediately with steamed rice.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, lemon juice and food coloring. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package; drain.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream into hot noodles. Place layer of noodle mixture in 9 x 13-inch buttered dish. Cover with layer of meat mixture.
Repeat process.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream bar cake
directions: Unwrap and layer ice cream sandwiches in a long dish. Pour caramel topping over the sandwiches. Sprinkle with nuts. Cover with Cool Whip. Cover and freeze.

title: ham pie
directions: Place cubed ham and diced eggs into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Melt butter in a saucepan with flour and seasoning, mixing until smooth.
Do not allow to brown.
Add milk and stir until smooth. Pour over ham and egg mixture.
Top with your favorite pie crust recipe.
(I use a regular purchased pie crust.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: smooth pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; blend in butter.
Add liquid ingredients, then eggs, one at a time.
Grease and flour tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: honey sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: cocoa-banana muffinettes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 30 miniature muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with nonstick cooking spray. Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add combined bananas, milk, margarine, egg whites and vanilla, mixing just until moistened.
Fill prepared cups almost full.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let muffins stand a few minutes; remove from pan.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: prune whip
directions: Dissolve jello in hot prune juice.
When partly set, beat until frothy.
Add prune pulp and continue beating.
Fold in whipping cream, whipped.

title: tuna-artichoke salad
directions: Combine tuna, artichokes, mushrooms and celery. Mix mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice, Worcestershire and onion salt. Gently stir into tuna and vegetables. Cover and refrigerate. Serve in a large tomato cup or with tomato slices. Yield: 4 servings.

title: our special holiday punch
directions: Core, peel and dice pineapple; slice lemons thin.
Place in bowl.
Add sugar and Cognac; let stand overnight.
Four hours before serving, add tea, rum and brandy; pour over block of ice in punch bowl.
Before serving, pour in champagne and sparkling water.
Add cherries.
Stir gently and serve.
Serves about 45 people.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove yolks from the hard-boiled eggs; mix with vinegar and seasoning or with boiled dressing.
Refill whites with yolks.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese. Add jello, water, pineapple and baby food.
Cook until blended. Cool in the refrigerator. Add Cool Whip and fold it in.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch dish and top with nuts.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O per directions, add crushed pineapple and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let chill a little while.
Put marshmallows on top of Jell-O.
Mix cream cheese and 1 packet of Dream Whip.
Put on top of Jell-O.
Top with grated cheese and chill.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and eggs.
Sift Sweet N' Low with flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add bananas, oats, nuts and raisins, coconut and chopped candied fruit cake mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar with shortening.
Add egg and pineapple. Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° approximately 10 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper and cool.

title: marinated brisket
directions: Put brisket in plastic cooking bag.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over meat in bag.
Close bag tightly and marinate 24 hours, turning several times.
Leave in bag.
Make 5 or 6 small slits in bag and cook in 275° oven for 5 to 6 hours. To serve, remove meat from bag and slice trimming excess fat. Skin marinade to remove fat and serve with meat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until needed.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter; cook until it starts to boil.
When boiling all over, remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter, salt and vanilla to mixture.
Mix until creamy.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet.

title: easy fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Mix peaches, sugar and flour.
Pour in 9 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish and top with stick of butter, cut in slices.
Break pie crust in pieces and place on top to cover.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Cream sugar, egg and butter for 5 minutes.
Blend with Cool Whip and add pineapple.
Add apples and nuts just before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla, cocoa, salt and eggs. Beat together, add food coloring and 2 jars water.
Add flour. Mix soda and vinegar and let settle.
Add buttermilk then soda and vinegar.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and keep refrigerated.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cabbage
directions: Blend milk and mayonnaise together in saucepan.
Add sugar, prepared mustard and vinegar.
Mix thoroughly while heating slowly.
Cut cabbage into quarters and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain cabbage thoroughly, place on platter and pour the hot dressing over cabbage.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: addictive peanut butter gems
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down.
Pour melted chocolate over top.
Chill and cut into small squares.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: texas meatballs
directions: Mix beef, sausage, bread crumbs and eggs.
Shape into small meatballs.
Brown in skillet; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until sauce is thick, stirring occasionally.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Top with cream cheese,
mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mixture.
Sprinkle mixed vegetables over this and top with grated carrots and grated cheese.
Chill and serve.
Cut into small pieces for a great appetizer.
We like this for Thanksgiving and Christmas for our evening meal with soup.

title: pam chicken casserole
directions: In casserole dish, mix all ingredients except the cheese. Mix well, then sprinkle with cheese. Bake about 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: hot cheese balls
directions: Shred cheese or let all ingredients stand at room temperature. Mix and work with hands into small balls.
Can be put on cookie sheet and frozen separately.
Put in plastic bag and use as needed.
Cook in hot oven at 425° for about 10 or 15 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes approximately 6 1/2 dozen balls.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla. Cook on low heat, stirring constantly for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Serve over ice cream, cake, etc.

title: gingerbread boy christmas cookie
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together; add egg and molasses and mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Wrap dough mixture in wax paper and chill overnight.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch and cut out.
Place on sprayed cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool before decorating.
Double or triple recipe.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, extract, egg and water.
Roll 1/4 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water and cool.
Add pineapple.
Let cool until partially congealed and spread on salad.

title: frito salad
directions: Add to lettuce, tomatoes, beans, chips and cheese, then add marinated onion and bell peppers in Catalina dressing for about 15 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(microwave)
directions: Melt butter in a 9-inch round cake pan 30 seconds on High. Stir in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple rings over syrup.
Place a cherry in center of each ring.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions substituting reserved pineapple syrup for water. Place pan on inverted saucer in microwave.
Microwave on Low, 7 to 9 minutes.
turn at least once.
Microwave on High, 3 to 4 minutes or until cake starts leaving sides of pan and toothpick in center comes out clean.
Center may have spots that look uncooked.
Let stand directly on countertop 1 to 2 minutes.
Loosen edges with knife and invert onto serving plate.

title: fresh strawberry frosting
directions: Clean strawberries and cut in quarters.
Sprinkle with sugar. Set to one side until sugar is dissolved.
Take potato masher and mash up strawberries.
Soften gelatin in water in a cup; dissolve until clear.
Stir into strawberries.
Chill and when partially set, fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top and sides of angel food cake.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: meatless taco salad
directions: Spread broken lettuce in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Spread tomatoes and green onions over lettuce. Spread drained beans over lettuce. Pour salad dressing over top.
When ready to serve, spread cheese over mixture, then top with crushed corn chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble meat in a 2-quart dish.
Cook in microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes.
Stir to break apart; drain.
Stir in rest of ingredients; shape into balls (1 teaspoon each).
Can store in freezer up to 2 weeks only.

title: layered chicken bake
directions: In 2-quart oblong baking dish, combine soups, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into quarters, cutting almost but not all the way through the bottom.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken mixture.
Bake 15 minutes more or until biscuits are golden brown and filling is hot and bubbling.
tags: Campbell's condensed creamy chicken mushroom soup

title: egg pie
directions: Heat the milk.
Add the beaten eggs and the sugar.
Pour the mixture in the pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cook at 350° for one hour.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix and pour over chicken in a large bowl. Refrigerate. Marinate for 12 to 24 hours. Flip occasionally. Heat grill to high.
Add chicken and lower temperature to medium heat.
Turn chicken and baste with remaining marinade for about 1 hour or desired crispness.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan bring to boil water, bouillon, and vegetables until vegetables are tender.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Blend all in blender.
Slightly blend to reduce size of vegetables.
(Omit this step of cooling and blending if you desire large chunks of vegetables in soup.)
Return to saucepan.
Add Rotel and Velveeta. Do not boil.
Heat on low and serve.
Freezes well.
One serving is one cup.

title: cottage cheese dressing
directions: Grate carrot in electric blender.
Add cottage cheese and milk, cover and process at high speed until smooth.
Turn mixture into medium bowl; stir in remaining ingredients.
If blender is not available, press cottage cheese through a sieve into a bowl, shred carrot, and stir in remaining ingredients.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes; pat dry.
Prick each potato with a fork in a few places.
Bake potatoes on a rack at 400° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Cut a thin slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out the pulp into a bowl.
Mash the potato pulp with the hot milk or half and half until fluffy.
Beat in the butter and the green onion.
Add seasonings.
Crumble Stripples. Add to potato mixture.
Spoon potato mixture into shells. Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Place potatoes on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until potatoes are piping hot and cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate mousse(portuguese)
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

Blend in cream, vanilla and salt. Gradually add to egg yolks, beating with wire whip until thick and creamy. Beat egg whites until foamy throughout. Gradually beat sugar and continue beating until mixture will form stiff peaks. Gently but thoroughly fold into chocolate mixture.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes or bowl.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 4 cups or 8 to 10 servings.

title: "warren's" fire cracker
directions: You will need 1 tall glass.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Pour hot water over gelatin and dissolve.
Chill until it begins to jell.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with fork; pour on frosting while cake is warm.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Combine cold vermicelli with m.s.g., seasoned salt, lemon juice and vegetable oil.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Combine remaining ingredients with pasta mixture.
Toss to coat and evenly distribute vegetables.

title: oatmeal hermits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except
potato chips, together and place in greased baking dish.
Top
with crushed potato chips. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add powdered sugar to taste. Keep refrigerated.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Beat egg yolks, salt and mustard until light and lemon colored.
Add oil, a small amount at a time.
Beat until mixture is emulsified.
Stir in lemon juice or vinegar.
Refrigerate until needed.
Makes 1 pint.

title: macaroni-cheese-corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally to mix all ingredients well as the butter and cheese melt.
Let sit for 10 minutes before serving.
Children especially enjoy this casserole.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix and place in muffin tins. Bake at 400° until golden brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Use a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Add first 7 ingredients and shake.
Let stand while you continue.
Cook pasta; rinse thoroughly in cold water.
Mix pasta with remaining ingredients. Add dressing; toss together and marinate for 2 hours in fridge. Serve on a bed of lettuce with tomato wedges.

title: banana split dessert(you will split for this recipe.  this dessert is made in layers.)
directions: Mix butter and cracker crumbs, then place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 2 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: very old punch recipe
directions: Combine all ingredients and let come to a simmer.
Strain. Serve hot.
Never fails.

title: chocolate-caramel brownies
directions: Unwrap caramels.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, pecans, 1/3 cup milk and melted margarine.
Press half of batter into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
In top of double boiler over simmering water, melt caramels with 1/2 cup milk.
When well mixed, pour over baked layer.
Cover with chocolate morsels.
Pour remaining batter on top of morsels.
Return to preheated 350° oven and bake for 18 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Empty pineapple and juice in a bowl.
Add pudding mix until well blended.
Blend in Cool Whip.

title: sunshine tea
directions: Boil sugar and cold water together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add 1 quart hot water and tea bags.
Steep for 5 more minutes.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Garnish cups with sliced lemons and mint sprigs.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter and cheese in cooked broccoli.
Mix 1/2 stick butter and stuffing mix and put on top of broccoli. Bake at 325°
for 20 minutes.

title: tallerina pie
directions: Brown pepper and onion in fat; add meat and brown.
Add corn, noodles, tomato paste and seasoning.
Let simmer a few minutes. Pour in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lauri's egg rolls
directions: Brown beef and pork; drain fat.
Drain shrimp.
Add peanut butter and m.s.g. to meat.
In wok, put sweet and sour sauce and salt.
Steam vegetables until tender.
Add meat; stir.
You may need more sweet and sour sauce and peanut butter.
Roll in egg roll skins.
Seal with water.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: coconut pecan pan
directions: Pour 1/4 of the cheese mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 caramel sauce on each.
Sprinkle 1/4 coconut mixture on each. Repeat layers.
Freeze 5 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add the molasses and well beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Roll into small balls (size of a walnut); dip or roll in granulated sugar and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned on bottom.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool and slice.
Combine other ingredients and mix well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: parmesan cutlets
directions: Brown pork chops or cutlets on both sides.
Place meat in a baking pan and cover with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cherry mashes
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cherry frosting, oleo, vanilla, condensed milk, cherries and food coloring until well blended.
Roll into small balls (about walnut size) and freeze.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin and add peanuts in double boiler.
Dip the cherry balls in it.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Before baking, sprinkle chocolate chips on top of cake.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed prunes
directions: Place
prunes
in
saucepan.
Cover with water; bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain, set aside. Combine cottage cheese, peanuts and orange rind, mixing well. Spoon
mixture
into
a
pastry bag with large tip, pipe into cavity
of each cooled prune.
Garnish with peanut halves by putting a little softened cream cheese on top of each filled prune to place peanut halves onto prunes.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Mix together; heat and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple surprises
directions: Cut celery into strips.
Spread peanut butter on it, then put raisins on it to make the ants.
That's all.

title: newport beef casserole
directions: In hot oil, using a large skillet, saute onions, garlic, carrot and celery until onion is golden, about 5 minutes.
Add beef; cook, stirring until red color disappears.
Add mushrooms, sherry, tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
If desired, cool, cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: quick sandwich filling
directions: Mix together and use as filling for sandwiches.
This makes a great sandwich filling for finger sandwiches.

title: lynn martin's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef.
Saute onions and garlic.
Pour off grease. Mix everything together, adding seasonings to taste.
Cook on medium heat
for
an hour.
Stir often to prevent sticking to the pan.

title: cream style corn
directions: Cut 22 cups raw sweet corn off cob.
Put corn in large roaster.
Pour in half and half.
Cut butter into 1/2 cubes and stir in sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Ready to eat or cool in cold water and place in bags to freeze.

title: pretzels
directions: Put water in bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir.
Add salt, sugar and flour.
Mix and knead dough with hands.
Roll and twist into pretzels.
Place on greased cookie sheet and brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
After mixing thoroughly, make into a loaf and place in a loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: batman delight
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan and add brown sugar until it all melts.
Take off heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternately add flour and eggs.
Mix carefully in the vanilla and nuts.
Do not beat.
Put into well buttered pan and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: easy party punch
directions: Delicious and easy!
Chill each separately, then mix when ready to serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spinach stuffed sole
directions: Defrost sole.
Cook spinach and drain well. Spread spinach and ham on fish.
Roll and place in greased casserole dish.
Drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vt.  apple banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add apples, then bananas.
Mix well again.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes "quite" clean.
Should be quite moist.

title: cuban black bean soup
directions: Prepare marinated rice.
Set aside for 1 hour or until next day; bring to room temperature before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and soda; blend. Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs and mix well. Add green chillies and cheese; stir. Pour in greased 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 375° for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: fresh green beans with cream of mushroom soup
directions: Cut green beans into bite size.
Boil about 1 quart of water for 5 minutes and take out.
Put green beans in casserole and pour can of cream of mushroom soup.
Put in oven or microwave for about 2 minutes.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cut dates in pieces; cook with 1/2 cup sugar, water and nutmeats until thickened.
Cool.
Meanwhile, blend shortening with sugars.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Roll dough 1/2 to 1/4 inch thickness and spread with filling.
Roll like jelly roll and store in refrigerator 4 hours.
Slice and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: lisa's penne pasta
directions: Bring water to boil. Add salt and pasta.
Cook for 8 minutes until al dente.

title: gramma schepman's cheese ball
directions: Soften the cheeses in bowl and mix well.
Add Worcestershire sauce, nuts and olives.
Put in refrigerator to stiffen.
Scoop out onto waxed paper and shape into ball.
Roll in more crushed nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: party dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in 3 pieces.
Cut bacon into 2 pieces.
Wrap bacon around hot dogs and secure with toothpicks.
Place in crock-pot and cook on high for 2 to 3 hours.
Place brown sugar on top.

title: overnight coffee loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar and salt.
Cut in 1 cup butter until mixture looks like meal.
Mix yeast, egg yolks and milk until dough is smooth.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip and put into pie crusts.
Pour blueberries on top.
Makes two pies.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and stir well.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into 9-inch pie pan; set aside.

title: brownie mounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix butter and sugar. Stir in corn syrup and eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Mix, then add melted chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto greased sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust; cover with top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes; cool 10 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Make dough stiff enough to roll out.
Cut and bake.
When cool, frost.
These are really good.
They can be frosted with just powdered sugar icing.

title: sausage stuffing for turkey
directions: Cook celery and onion with beef and sausage; drain off fat. In large bowl or pan, put croutettes and wet with hot water until soft, not soppy.
Add meat mixture and stir until all thoroughly mixed.
Stuff bird.

title: meats chicken paprika
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Combine oil, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well, then roll pieces of chicken in mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until chicken is done.

title: almond punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Mix all ingredients, except 7-Ups.
Just before serving, add 7-Ups.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Place half of bread cubes in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Add cream cheese cubes.
Add remaining bread cubes.
Combine beaten eggs, milk and maple syrup.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Delicious!

title: cheese crisps
directions: Grate cheese; add to softened butter or oleo.
Mix well.
Add flour and pepper.
Mix well.
Add cereal and mix with hands. Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
