Press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: mildew on shower curtain
directions: Soak the garment in warm vinegar and water.

title: breast of chicken supreme
directions: After seasoning chicken with salt and pepper, saute gently in butter until lightly browned and partly cooked.
Place ham slices on bottom of large baking pan and put sauteed chicken breasts on top.
Saute mushroom slices and add to chicken.
Next add water chestnuts and the mixture of mushroom soup, grapes and wine. Cover casserole with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add brown sugar gradually. Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Sift flour with salt and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in rolled oats and coconut. Form into two 2-inch rolls and chill thoroughly.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350°
oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas and cookies in pan, 9 x 12-inch.
Cook other ingredients until thick.
Spoon over bananas and cookies.
Top with egg whites.
Brown in oven
on broil.
Chill and serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together and roll into approximately 65 balls. (Mixture should be stiff.) Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Cover batter and store in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: wanda's potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix potatoes, onion, sour cream, cheese and soup together well. Place in large casserole. Mix corn flakes and butter together and place on top of potato mixture. Bake 1 1/2 hours. Serves 10.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients in mixing bowl and make well in center. Combine egg and milk.
Melt shortening, cool slightly and add to egg mixture.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop batter from tablespoon into greased muffin pans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: krispy kissies
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peak forms, then add in cream of tartar and slowly add brown sugar, beating after each addition. Add vanilla and beat, then slowly fold in Rice Krispies with wooden spoon or plastic spatula.
Spray cookie sheet and spoon by tablespoon leaving 1/2 inch space.
Bake in a 250° oven 30 minutes. Turn off oven and leave in oven 30 minutes.
Do not open oven at any time until completely finished.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite snack:  peanut butter and jelly
directions: You take the bread and you put peanut butter on it, then put jelly on it, and swirl it around.
And then you have a peanut butter and jelly sandwich.
Enjoy!

title: cheese and bacon puffs
directions: Combine water and butter in a heavy saucepan, bring to a boil.
Add flour, salt and peppers.
Cook, beating with a wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth ball. Remove from heat, cool 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in cheese, bacon and green onions.

title: stuffed zucchini shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Drain and return to pot filled with cold water.

title: chonny's pork stir-fry
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Cut vegetables into small pieces. Place oil in frying pan; heat to medium-high.
Brown meat.
Add carrots, celery and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cinnamon.
Add mushrooms and soy sauce.
Cook until mushrooms are tender.
Add snow peas.
Cook until hot.
Serve over white rice.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Scald 3/4 cup of the half and half in double boiler.
Add remaining milk to beaten egg yolks in a small bowl.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir egg mixture into scalded milk.
Whisk and add dry ingredients carefully, whisking into scalded mix.
Cook until thick.
Remove from fire.
Heat vinegar and whisk into cooked mixture.
May be stored in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: italian string beans
directions: Cover ingredients in pan.
Boil, reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender.
After 1 hour, meatballs may be added, if desired.

title: eagle brand delicious cookie bar
directions: Melt oleo.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs. Top with chips. Press down firmly. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown. Cool. Cut into bars. Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes cut sides upon baking sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over tomato halves.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven about 12 minutes or until crumbs are golden.

title: lazarus' zucchini bread with strawberry cream cheese
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add zucchini.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to oil mixture and blend lightly.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat together the peanut butter, brown sugar, egg and baking soda until the mixture is smooth and well blended. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop the dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet, spacing the mounds about 2-inches apart.

Bake one pan at a time in a 350° oven until the cookies are puffed and slightly golden, but still soft to the touch (about 10 minutes). Let cookies cool on the baking sheet for about 5 minutes. Transfer cookies to a wire rack; let cool completely.

title: oriental chicken kabobs
directions: In a bowl combine all marinade ingredients and mix well.
Add chicken cubes and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.
After chicken has marinated, grill chicken over hot coals, turning often, until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Makes creamy dressing that will not separate.
Wonderful!

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and dry.
Hard-boil eggs; fry the bacon until crispy and cool.
Chop white parts of eggs and set aside.
In a shaker jar, mix vinegar, oil, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Shake well.
Pour over spinach, torn in bite size pieces.
Toss. Sprinkle on egg whites and bacon.
Serve.

title: baked pork chops and potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes in a baking dish; top with onions, then top with pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil and bake 20 minutes.

title: cool whip graveyard treat
directions: Mix 2 cups of the cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly onto bottom of pan. Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup of sugar in bowl until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice. Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Spread remaining whipped topping over gelatin.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.
Decorate as a graveyard, if desired. Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: cole slaw salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together very good and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: perfect pie meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gradually beat in sugar until blended good.
Spread meringue over pie.
Be sure to put over crust, sealing filling in.
Bake at 425° for 4 to 5 minutes or until light brown.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain.
Return noodles to pan, stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: egg-cheese-sausage casserole(great for brunch)
directions: Mix up all ingredients the night before.
You must refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh corn chowder
directions: Cut corn off the cob.
Set aside.
In saucepan, saute onions and celery in butter.
Add potatoes, water, chicken bouillon and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine flour and milk until smooth.
Gradually stir into soup.
Bring to boil, cook and stir until thicken.
Salt /Pepper to taste.

title: chess cake
directions: Carrots, pineapple and raisins team up for nutritious, homemade goodness.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter lightly the bottom and sides of sheet cake pan.
Pour in pineapple, cherry pie filling, cake mix, brown sugar, nuts and butter.
Do not mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine the corn meal, flour, salt, chili powder, oregano and pepper. Dip chicken in milk, then roll in the corn meal mixture. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Drizzle with butter. Bake uncovered for 50 to 55 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and remainder of ingredients.
Pour into two (2) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican soup
directions: Mix together. Bring to simmer. Simmer for about 1 hour. Serve with cheese sprinkled on top. Can use Cheddar and Monterey Jack. Yields 12 cups.

title: stuffed mirlitons
directions: Boil mirlitons (whole) until tender.
Cut in halves lengthwise.
Gently scoop the pulp out of shells.
Put the shells in a baking pan or dish.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and cocoa.
Beat in the eggs.
Blend the flour, soda and salt and add to the shortening mixture alternately with the applesauce.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour batter into a jelly roll pan.
Before baking, sprinkle chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts over the mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: evelyn's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs.

title: chicken cordon bleu(easy)
directions: Pound chicken with meat mallet until flattened evenly so that they will cook evenly.
Mix mayo and milk in small bowl until smooth.
Dip chicken in mixture, then dip both sides in bread crumbs.
Chicken will be in the shape of a triangle.
Place opening down in a baking pan.
Sprinkle top with parsley flakes.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: chicken a la maude
directions: Saute green onion, celery, and green pepper 3 to 4 minutes. Add white sauce to a 3-quart pot.
Add all remaining ingredients to sauce.
Mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon.
Serve over boiled rice.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine together.
Cool.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
Make two rolls and roll in coconut.
Chill until firm and slice.

title: cauliflower marranga
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter and juice of 1 lemon.
Cut cauliflower in flower pieces and saute with 3 cloves crushed garlic, basil and salt and pepper.
Combine rice, salted and buttered, with cheese and other ingredients.

title: broccoli-bacon-raisin salad
directions: Break broccoli into small flowerets.
Mix the broccoli, onion, celery, bacon, raisins and sunflower seeds together in a large salad bowl and set aside.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs slightly in small bowl.
Add next ingredients; beat just until well blended.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into well-greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: baked fish italian
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread crumbs and Italian seasoning in sealed sandwich bag.
Pour dressing into bowl.
Dip fish in dressing to coat.
Place in sandwich bag (1 piece at a time).
Shake to coat fish.
Spray baking dish with butter flavor Pam.
Place fish on baking dish.
Bake until fish flakes easily (15 to 18 minutes).
Remove from oven.
Spray quickly with butter spray.
Serve immediately.
Each serving:
169 calories; 1 gm. fat.

title: chicken supreme(serves 12)
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Lay dried beef in bottom of glass dish.
Lay chicken breasts on top.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours without a lid.

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Crumble crackers very fine.
Cut pepper, onion and celery in chunks and put in blender.
Blend on high.
Combine all ingredients except cheeses and catsup; mix well.
Use a large baking dish, one with a rack, if available.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and oatmeal powder.
Then add salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together chips, chocolate and nuts, then fold it into batter.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Press dough into a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in 2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread on the cookie crust.
Garnish with suggested toppings as desired.
Serve immediately or refrigerate to serve.

title: fancy banana dessert
directions: Combine pudding, milk, brown sugar and vanilla in a medium size saucepan.
Mix well and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and is thick.
Remove from heat and chill.

title: chuck wagon carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a 2-quart microwave bowl.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook on High in microwave for 8 minutes.
(Stir halfway through cook time.)
Drain carrots and add butter and onions, cooking for 50 seconds on High.
Add all other ingredients and cook an additional 4 minutes, stirring halfway through.

title: dilly broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Stir in butter and dill weed.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: bananas with syrup threads(hot glaze bananas)
directions: Peel and cut the bananas into large cubes slantwise.
Fry the bananas in deep oil until golden brown.
Remove the bananas to a plate.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in pan and add sugar.
Stir on a medium fire until it melts.
Cook two minutes more until the sugar forms into a thick syrup.
Add the fried bananas and mix well. Serve immediately while very hot.

title: quick dinner
directions: In a microwave cook potatoes according to directions on package.
Add sauce package and milk as directed.
Stir in eggs, ham and peas.
Cover with wax paper or microwave paper.
Cook on High, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves four.

title: egg fondue
directions: Saute sausage until meat is no longer red.
Drain.
Put bread, sausage and cheese in layers in a casserole dish.
Pour milk, eggs, salt and mustard mixture over it and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Makes a 3-quart casserole.
Be sure casserole dish is only 3/4 full.
May be prepared the night before, or frozen and baked later.

title: peanut butter brownie torte bars
directions: Mix brownie mix, water, oil and egg together.
Stir in chopped peanuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch or spring-form pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done at 350°.
Cool completely.
Mix together powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Spread over brownie. Melt chocolate and butter together.
Spread over peanut butter layer.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
If you use a spring-form pan, cut into wedges and serve as an elegant, easy dessert.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 15-inch pan or dish.
Cover bottom with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk; beat until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread 1/2 mixture over graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers and add remaining mixture over second layer of crackers.
Place another layer of crackers on top.

title: crawfish or shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in 1/4 ??? vegetable oil until tender (low heat).
Add cooked meat or seafood (1 to 2 ounces sausage; optional) and saute 5 to 7 minutes.
Add 1 cup water and simmer 1 hour.
(Add a little more water as it boils to tenderize mixture.)
Season to taste (I use Tony Chachere's Cajun seasoning mixture).
Add rice and steam slowly in covered pot for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Clean the beans of any rocks or bad beans.
Rinse.
Put in large pot and cover with 4 to 5 inches of water.
Place over heat; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low simmer.
Cook 2 hours.
Add salt and margarine.
Continue cooking 30 minutes to 1 hour until beans are tender.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, dill weed, garlic powder and Hidden Valley Ranch mix. Pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Seal and let stand several hours.

title: after school mix
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, melt chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir frequently until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Place cereal in a large bowl.
Pour melted chocolate and peanut butter over cereal.
Stir to coat.
Place cereal and sugar in large, clean paper bag.
Shake to coat. Pour cereal out onto cookie sheet to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: easy taco burgers
directions: In skillet, scramble and brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain all fat.
Add tomato paste, taco mix, onion soup mix and water. Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Spoon onto buns.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and
dice
up.
Mix
together
sour cream, green onions and half the
cheese.
Baste tortillas with green enchilada sauce.
Spread
the
sour cream mix on the tortillas and put chicken on top of it.
Roll up and place in pan.
Pour the remaining sauce on top, then sprinkle the remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: "treasure chest"
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, nuts, brown sugar and butter together.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in an oblong Tupperware about the size of a cake pan.
Put the 1/2 gallon of ice cream on this, then top with rest of crumbs.
Freeze.
Best if taken out of freezer about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a small bowl, beat eggs. In a large bowl, cream the butter. Add sugar gradually. Add beaten eggs. Mix flour with baking powder. Dredge fruit and nuts with 1 cup flour. Set aside.

title: dimple's banana pudding
directions: Follow instructions on pudding box, cutting milk 1/2 c.
Beat no longer than 2 minutes.
Add:
Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer chunks of wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat. Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry blender salad
directions: Mix jello in water.
Chill 20 minutes.
Put thawed strawberries, drained pineapple and bananas in blender.
Blend a few seconds at a time until smooth.
Combine with jello mixture. Mix well.
Pour in bowl or pan.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In saucepan, heat until well blended the tuna, milk, celery and mushroom soups.
Pour over noodles.
Sprinkle cheese over all in a casserole.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grape-nuts flakes cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and maple flavoring; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, coconut, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Stir in Grape-Nuts flakes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned in 375° oven. Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease tube pan well with margarine.

Put rolls around pan; alternate 2 tablespoons pudding, 1/2 sugar mixture and 1/2 brown sugar and alternate again. Sprinkle melted butter all over top. Cover with tinfoil and leave on stove overnight. (If rolls are not up to the top of the pan, put over a pan of hot water.)
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take off foil and bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover plate well with foil and turn onto dish.

title: baked rice
directions: Slightly brown onion in butter, then add dried rice and brown a little more, about 2 minutes.
Turn into casserole dish.
Add broth, mushrooms, curry and parsley flakes.
Stir, then add butter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Stir to fluff.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Add sugar, molasses, egg and Crisco (cooled).
Add flour, etc. Chill overnight.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Put on greased sheet 2 inches apart, pressed down with small glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.
If you take the cookies out of the oven about a minute before they're done and let them sit on sheet about a minute, they're more chewy.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Combine hash brown mix and water.
Stir well and let stand covered for 15 minutes; drain.
Wrap tortillas securely in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Combine hash browns, eggs, sausage, salt and pepper; stir well. Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add egg mixture; cook over low heat, stirring gently until eggs are set.
Fill each tortilla with 1/2 cup egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up, placing seam side down.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter and milk, plus flavoring, together. Add flour slowly.
Knead dough.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° on greased baking sheet.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Graham cracker crust can also be used.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Preferably over a wood fire, heat margarine until melted. Saute diced onion until brown.
Add wine and saute beef.
Add water to completely cover potatoes.
When added, slow boil until done, then add carrots, salt and pepper.
If cooking over a wood fire, the best way leave pot cover part way off to encourage smoke from fire to flavor stew.
If cooked on a stove, continue to cook with no cover.
Several hours are required, then stew will be thick enough to eat with a fork.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Heat in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix brown sugar, butter or margarine, white corn syrup and salt.
Microwave on High until boiling, then cook 2 minutes longer.
Gently stir in baking soda. Pour syrup over popped corn in a paper grocery bag.
Close, shake and microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes, shake, microwave High 1 1/2 minutes.
May need to repeat a third time.
Pour caramel corn onto cookie sheet to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Chocolate chips or raisins may be used for variety.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sift and mix the flour, sugar, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add the milk and mix. Pour over the melted margarine. Drain the peaches and pour on top of the mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add milk and well beaten egg.
Stir.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and boil 2 minutes.
Continue to stir.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, rice and raisins.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: nacho cheese sauce
directions: Melt cheese in crock-pot on low or in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low in crock-pot for 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Serve over chips (tortilla).

title: quick and easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a microwave dish.
Microwave 5 minutes, then add 1 tsp. vanilla and 2 Tbsp. butter.
Microwave 5 more minutes and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Fry bacon.
Heat beans in bacon grease.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Add picante, garlic, oregano and crumbled bacon. Serve with taco chips.
May be refrigerated several days.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across grain into very thin, 1/2-inch long strips. In large skillet, heat oil.
Saute beef until tender.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Stir and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in mushroom soup, beef consomme, water, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream. Cook noodles.

title: peanut butter chocolate kisses cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, peanut butter and butter in mixing bowl; beat until thoroughly blended.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend well. Add flour; blend well.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour. Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets from oven and press chocolate kiss in center of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 3 minutes.
Watch carefully to avoid burning chocolate.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Cool completely before storing.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift all of the dry ingredients together into an ungreased 8-inch sq. pan.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients; mix well. Stir in the chicken. Cover and refrigerate for at least
1 hour.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cut cheese in small pieces, melt with other ingredients in double boiler.
Stir often.
Enjoy with tostado chips.

title: californian enchilada pie
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Add onion with garlic.
Saute until golden.
Add hamburg; brown.
Sprinkle flour over cooked meat and stir to blend.
Add tomato sauce, bouillon, vinegar, chili powder and salt.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Have corn tortillas ready (don't fry, use as is).
Line long casserole with 2 or 3 tortillas.
Pour some of the sauce over these tortillas.
Next, sprinkle with some chopped onion, grated cheese and olives, then repeat the process.
Cover top with extra cheese and you can mix cheeses if you wish (Jack cheese and Cheddar).
Dot with a few whole black olives.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly at 350°.
Serve with salad, Pepsi or light beer, sherbet for dessert and garlic bread.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions. Drain fat off meat. Add in large pot the meat, beans, soup, tomatoes, water, tomato sauce and seasoning. Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to pie directions. Fold in 3/4 of cool whip, and stir until uniform in color. Pour 1/2 into each pie shell. Top with cool whip. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

title: a quick lunch(lo-cal)
directions: Heat sauerkraut, toast your slice of bread and open tuna. Place your toast on a small plate.
Add sauerkraut and sprinkle with your tuna.
This and a small bowl of vegetable crispies: tomato wedge, pepper ring, onion ring, celery stick, carrot stick, etc.
A very filling lunch.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Fry sausage. Drain grease. Add soup. Add 1 can water (less water to make thicker). Simmer.

title: pollo con naranja(chicken with orange)
directions: Advance Preparation:
Brown chicken in hot butter or oil in skillet.
Remove chicken.
Add flour, salt and spices to skillet, stirring to form a paste.
Add orange
juice and Tabasco sauce. Stir constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add chicken, raisins and almonds.
Cover tightly.
(May be refrigerated overnight.)

title: cranberry minty punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, mint and cranberry sauce in an electric blender; whirl until smooth.
Chill until ready to serve. At serving time, pour over ice in a large pitcher or small punch bowl.
Slowly stir in ginger ale.
Serve in punch cups.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: tea party punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Combine sugar syrup, fruit juices and tea in large container; mix well.
Chill until ready to serve.
Yields 40 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt cheese with soup.
Add tomatoes.
Mix all with hominy. Pour into buttered casserole dish; add crushed Fritos over top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fried pink salmon
directions: Remove large bones from salmon.
Mix all ingredients together. Mix well.
Fry in hot vegetable oil or lard.

title: garden soup
directions: In saucepan, over high heat, combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra firmly in hot sterilized jars.
Put a garlic bud in each jar.
Meanwhile, combine vinegar, water, salt, peppers and dill seed and bring to a boil.
Pour the boiling brine into jars over okra.
Adjust caps and seal.
Yields 4 to 5 pints.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large saucepan with 4 to 6 cups boiling water, cook macaroni until tender.
Drain; stir in mayonnaise until macaroni is creamy.
Set aside to cool.
In separate bowl, dice vegetables into bite sizes.
When macaroni is cooled, stir vegetables into macaroni and salt to taste.

title: country fried steak
directions: Combine the onion soup and hot water in bowl.
Brown the steak in the oil on both sides.
Remove the steak from skillet.
Add flour and stir.
Add the onion soup mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put the steak back into the skillet.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli or squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli or squash.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, egg and onion.
Add vegetable and mix.
Pour into dish. Cover with crackers you have sauteed in butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine the milk, sugar, oil and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 c. flour and beat well.
Beat egg in yeast mixture and gradually add the remaining flour.
Knead the dough on a floured surface for 10 minutes or you may use a dough hook.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning once to grease the dough all over.
Cover, place in a warm place to rise until doubled in bulk (1-2 hours).

title: crusty sweet potato casserole
directions: Add sugar, salt, margarine, vanilla, milk and the rest.
Mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: quick raisin rice pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine rice, raisins, sugar, salt and spices. Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir well a small amount of mixture into eggs.
Return to remaining mixture.
Cover tightly.
Let stand 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick lasagna
directions: In large casserole brown beef in butter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the spaghetti sauce mix.
Spoon cottage cheese over meat.
Top with noodles in a layer. Sprinkle with remaining spaghetti sauce mix, basil, parsley and salt.
Pour tomatoes, tomato sauce and water over top making sure all is moistened.
Sprinkle with cheese evenly topped.
Bake 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; boil 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients into mixture and drop on waxed paper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and peanut butter.
Add well beaten eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll out.
Cut.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Beat the eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until smooth.
Melt the butter; add the cocoa and stir until smooth.
Add butter and cocoa to the sugar and eggs and mix thoroughly.
Stir in the pecans, salt and flour and mix again. Place in a greased and floured shallow loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate (350°) oven about 20 minutes or until done.
Place marshmallows on top and melt in oven.
Cover with icing.

title: scallion pie
directions: Bring water to boil in large skillet over high heat.
Add green onions and cook, stirring, until green tops are wilted approximately 2 minutes, drain.
Add cream, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper to skillet.
Bring to boil and cook until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Set aside.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: To
drained
and
mashed potatoes, add cheese and other ingredients; blend well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch
square baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired. Bake
immediately
or cover and refrigerate.
If refrigerated, let stand
minutes	at
room
temperature.	Bake
at 325°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.	Serves 8.

title: amaretto dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except for fresh fruit.
Dip fresh fruits.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken and rice)
directions: Boil chicken with all the spices until almost done.
In a saute pan, combine oil, rice, tomato, onion, green pepper, wine and tomato sauce.
Saute until rice is light brown.
Add to chicken, cover and let simmer for 25 minutes.

title: ten minute bars
directions: Melt
butter;
pour
over sugar and oatmeal.
Mix well. Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Grease a cookie sheet with margarine and arrange one layer of soda crackers on the sheet.
In a saucepan, boil the brown sugar and butter for 3 minutes, stirring, then pour over the crackers. Bake for 5 minutes at 375°.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Spread over top as they melt. Top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Let cool and cut into pieces.
Very quick and with few ingredients.
Tastes delicious.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well in blender.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt oleo; add cocoa and stir.
Add sugar, eggs, flour, salt and pecans.
Mix and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread 1 jar Marshmallow Creme over hot cake.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Brown flour in oil.
Add paprika.
Slowly add 1/4 cup water to make a thick paste.
After lumps are worked out add remainder of ingredients and then let up with 4 1/4 cups water.
Cook slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: muscadine jam
directions: Remove stems and skins from muscadines. Cook pulp over low heat until soft; press through a sieve or food mill to remove seeds. Combine pulp and sugar in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil. Boil almost to jellying point (220°) about 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and skim off foam with a metal spoon. Ladle quickly into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Cover at once with metal lids and screw bands tight. Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes. Yield: about 3 pints.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Top with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Lay whole graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Put pudding and 3 cups milk in bowl.
Beat until thick. Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Spread 1/2 of pudding over crackers.
Lay more crackers over top.
Spread remaining pudding on crackers.
Top with one more layer of crackers.
Then mix melted chocolate, powdered sugar, Karo syrup, butter, 3 tablespoons milk and vanilla. Beat together and spread over top.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Clean and chop broccoli, celery and onions.
Cover with water and cook until tender, then add milk, water or mushroom soup, butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream the butter with the sugar and flour.
Mix ingredients together; pour into pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: banana cream pie(diet)
directions: Prepare pudding according to the directions on package; add banana extract.
Fold in half of the whipped topping.
Spoon into dish and top with remaining topping.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Serves 12.
In a glass pan, tear bite size portions of angel food cake to line bottom of pan.
Drain pineapple; save juice. Add pineapple juice and water to make one cup.
Bring to boil. Let cool.
Then add 2 packages of gelatin until dissolved.
Add pineapple to mixture and pour over cake.
Top with whipped topping and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: plum good cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use Caramel Frosting (optional).

title: great grandma's white sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Cut in butter (like when you make pie crust).
In smaller bowl, put eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; blend well.
Lastly, add sugar.
Beat until smooth and blended.
Pour into flour mixture; mix.
A little extra flour may be added now if dough isn't thick.
Roll out on floured board and cut in fancy shapes or roll in balls and crisscross with fork. Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Watch as can burn easily.

title: liver cookies for dogs and cats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Process liver in food processor or blender until liquified.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a bowl; add liver and stir well.
Drop by teaspoons on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Press tops down with a small glass dipped in cornmeal.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and freeze to use as needed.

title: no-yolk deviled eggs
directions: Spoon cottage cheese onto several layers of paper towels. Spread to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cover with additional paper towel. Let stand 5 minutes.
Scrape cottage cheese from paper towel.
Add cottage cheese, pickle relish and next 4 ingredients in processor and process until smooth.
Peel eggs.
Slice in half; remove yolks. Spoon filling mixture in egg white.
Sprinkle with paprika and fresh parsley.

title: rice roger chicken
directions: Flour and brown chicken in a little oil.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water. Put rice and salt in large flat casserole and sprinkle with grated onion. Add mushrooms and arrange chicken over all.
Pour bouillon over all and dot with butter.

title: salsa
directions: Cook ingredients for 45 minutes.
Process in jars for 20 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix chuck, bread crumbs, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Brown in skillet until cooked through.
In separate saucepan, melt the grape jelly on low heat.
Add chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce and remaining ingredients.
Heat and combine with meatballs.
Yields approximately 40 meatballs.

title: apricot casserole
directions: Drain apricots and put in 2-quart casserole (long flat dish). Cover with sugar and then cut butter into pieces and lay over sugar.
Break crackers into small pieces (but not fine pieces) and put on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Good served as a side dish to ham, turkey or chicken.
Also, can be served as a dessert.

title: sausage bites
directions: Have cheese and sausage at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients and form into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
(May be frozen before baking.)
Makes 100 (1-inch) balls.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together in large glass bowl (or Tupperware bowl).
Cover and place in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours or overnight.

title: chewies
directions: Mix well together the margarine, sugar, eggs, and flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put into a 9x13 inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: turkey bone soup
directions: Place bones from roasted turkey in a large Dutch oven.
Cover bones with cold water and cook 1/2 to 1 hour.
Remove bones and put the meat back into the Dutch oven.
Add the vegetables and seasonings.
Cook 30 more minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Add noodles and cook until done.

title: tuna patties or salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients until well combined and will hold together.
Shape into 4 to 6 patties.
Heat small amount oil in skillet.
Place patties into skillet.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Turn and continue frying until browned on both sides, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Cook onion with hamburger meat, set aside.
Drain off grease. Bring to boil soup, water and tomatoes.
Put a layer of slightly crushed Doritos on bottom of casserole dish that has been lightly greased.
Put a layer of hamburger mixture and layer of soup mixture, then another layer of Doritos, etc. until all ingredients are used.
Top with cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: jean's tortillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening.	Add enough cold water to make dough like biscuit dough.
Make little balls. Roll very thin, fry on hot griddle.
Grease griddle or iron skillet lightly for first tortilla.
After that just wipe skillet with paper towel.

title: bavarin
directions: Mix jello and hot water; add cold water and freeze until thickens.
Set aside 1/2 cup jello.
Mix ice cream with 1/2 cup jello.
Then top with other mixture and chill!

title: broccoli or cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice together and pour on top of vegetables.
Cook vegetables and topping in microwave for 8 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in oil.
Add hamburger.
Stir until hamburger is slightly browned; drain.
Add beans; let warm. Add tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can sprinkle diced onion and cheese over servings.

title: pasta delight
directions: In a 6-quart heavy saucepan or Dutch oven, cook linguini according to package directions until just tender.
Drain well. Return linguini to pot.
Add butter, ham, peas and mushrooms; set aside.

title: melting moments
directions: Cream soft butter or oleo and powdered sugar together.
Beat in cornstarch and sifted flour.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Form into 36 uneven heaps on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until very lightly brown on bottom, about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: never easier potato casserole
directions: Use a medium saucepan to boil water.
Sprinkle maize meal into boiling water, in small quantities.
Stir continuously until all the maize meal becomes a mixture of thick paste.
To make sure there are no lumps, use a wooden spade.
Continue stirring until the mixture is thick.
Cover it under very low heat for 10 minutes at the same time.
Stir every 3 minutes to make sure it does not stick to the saucepan.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato-tomato scallop
directions: Saute onion in butter until barely tender; stir in flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Add water, tomatoes and bouillon cubes. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bouillon cubes dissolve and mixture thickens.
Place potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add tomato mixture. Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Yields about 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday divinity
directions: In heavy medium saucepan, over low heat, cook and stir sugar, water and corn syrup until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat to medium.
Cook, without stirring, until a candy thermometer registers 268° (hard ball stage) or until small amount dropped into very cold water forms a ball.

title: hobo dinners or sunday school specials
directions: Tear off 4 large 14-inch squares of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Butter about 6 inches of it in the center.
Cut potato in 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick slices and place on the center of each piece of foil (one potato for each piece).
Cut carrot in 4-inch chunks and place on potato and onion, also.
Sprinkle veggies with seasonings, making sure all is seasoned.
Place salted ground chuck on top of all and fold foil over tightly.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 300°
while you are at Sunday School or elsewhere.
If you have long services, bake at 250°.
Ta-da! Dinner's ready when you get home.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate for 1 1/4 hours, until slightly thickened consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in whipped topping and wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes or until mixture mounds. Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into hot 6-cup mold.
To unmold, dip mold into hot water for about 15 seconds.
Gently pull gelatin from around edge with moist finger. Place moistened serving plate on top of mold; invert mold and plate.
Holding mold and plate together, shake slightly to loosen. Gently remove plate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini in salted water until tender but crisp.
Drain. Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients. Cook until cheese melts.
Pour over zucchini and top with 2 tablespoons melted butter, tossed with 1/2 cups cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: To make the crust, thinly slice chilled cookie dough to 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange slices closely together on ungreased 12 1/2-inch round pizza pan or oblong pan.
Let stand a few minutes to soften dough.
Press dough together to cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: marvin's squash
directions: Cut each squash into 8 sections lengthwise; place each cut squash into separate piece of foil and season with salt, pepper and Mrs. Dash.
Slice onions on top of each.
Add a pat of butter and seal foil.
Place on grill for about 30 minutes or until desired texture.

title: grandma stickney's custard
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Warm milk.
Beat eggs with sugar until thick and slowly pour warmed milk into the eggs.
Add salt and nutmeg to taste.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle generously with more nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: cozy cabin stew
directions: Mix soups together (no milk or water).
Mix in onion soup mix.
Add beef cubes.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Sour cream optional.
Boil noodles or rice according to directions.
Pour meat mixture over.

title: coconut cake icing
directions: Make 2 (8-inch) white cakes.
Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar together.
Slice 2 cakes in half, side to side.
Put icing between each layer, on top and on sides of cake.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into a cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Cover with melted butter.
Make sure butter covers all of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken to 1/8-inch thick.
Top each with slice of ham and cheese.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Brush with melted butter, then roll in crumbs to which a "smidge" of Parmesan cheese has been added.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
Excellent to keep in freezer uncooked up to 2 weeks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend together cream cheese, Blue cheese and Nucoa.
Cream until soft.
Add olives and green onions.
Chill slightly.
Roll into a ball.
Roll on 1/3 cup walnuts.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer while cooking spaghetti. Add meatballs (cooked), ground beef (cooked), mushrooms, sausage (cooked) - whatever you have on hand.
Serves 4.

title: better butter
directions: Use butter which is soft but not melted. Dissolve salt in water in blender. Add all other ingredients and blend until smooth. Pour into containers and store in refrigerator.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Blend cheese soup with milk and mayonnaise; add beans, celery, parsley, pimento and 1/2 can of the onion rings.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered.
Then uncover and bake for 10 more minutes with remaining onion rings on top.

title: topping for cake
directions: Bring Crisco, butter, sugar and milk to boil.
Add coconut and spread on warm cake and put under broiler slow to brown coconut, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: purple cow shake
directions: Put grape juice and ice cream in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed 10 to 15 seconds (or beat all ingredients with a hand beater).
Pour into tall glass.
Serve right away.
Serves 1.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into patties and grill.

title: levee's chocolate balls
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and milk.
Add vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Roll into small balls; put toothpick in each ball.
Place on cookie sheet.
Let stand in freezer all night.
Heat the Baker's chocolate (1/4 pound).
Heat one bar, less 1 inch, of Gulfwax with chocolate.
Dip balls in mixture with toothpick.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with chopped pecans and strawberries.
Keep frozen; take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients but cheese. Pour half into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread cheese over mixture.
Cover with rest of mixture.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: selma's soup from evie
directions: Brown onion and soup bone in a small amount of oil.
Add rest of ingredients, except sausage or wieners, and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.
To serve, heat soup with cubed sausage or wieners.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart casserole dish lightly with cooking oil spray. Spread chicken on bottom of dish.
In medium bowl, combine soup, sour cream, milk and noodles.
Pour over chicken.
In the same pot used to cook the noodles, melt the butter.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops (both sides); salt and pepper to taste.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Make noodles or rice and serve with sauce over noodles or rice with pork chops.

title: pooya bread(hot cajun cornbread)
directions: Mix everything.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, about 1/2-inch thick.
Batter will be rather "loose."
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until it begins to "brown" on top.
It should be sort of crisp when served.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine and combine with beef bouillon and consomme. Put rice in casserole dish and pour margarine mixture over top. Stir to mix well.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: little cornbread wraps
directions: Separate dough into strips.
Cut each strip in half.
Wrap dough around sausage link and press ends together to seal.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon jello(for a large crowd)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen lemonade. Mix and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Add frozen Cool Whip and mix with electric beater for 5 minutes.
Pour into bowls.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: peach bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add peach puree and dry ingredients; mix thoroughly. Add vanilla and nuts; stir until blended.
Pour into 2 loaf pans (5 x 9-inch) that have been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let bread cool a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: reese's fudge
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Remove from stove. Combine all ingredients. Press into 9-inch square pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: happy birthday coconut cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients; add remaining ingredients.
Beat 200 strokes on low speed of mixer (2 minutes by hand).
Scrape bowl often.
Add 1/4 cup milk and 2 unbeaten eggs.
Beat 200 strokes (same as before).
Pour into 2 (9-inch) round Crisco-coated layer pans (1 1/2-inches deep).
Bake until cakes test done.
Cool; remove from pans.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until translucent and tender.
Add onions, beef broth and spices to crock-pot and cook all day. Place 1/2 slice toasted bread in each of 8 oven-safe bowls.
Pour soup into bowls and place 1/2 slice of cheese over soup.
Broil in oven until brown.

title: "peggy's" banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package, then add 1 cup sour cream and 1/2 of large container of Cool Whip.
In 4-quart casserole, layer bananas, then layer of wafers, then layer of pudding mixture. Repeat until casserole is full, using all of pudding mixture and 7 or 8 bananas and a box of wafers.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Keeps well in refrigerator several days.
It gets better the second day!

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Shred cabbage.
In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook cabbage and salt until very tender.
Add water, if needed.
Cook hamburger and onion together; stir in spaghetti sauce, rice and water.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender about 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spoon 1/2 meat sauce mixture.
Top with 1/2 cabbage and 1/2 cheese; repeat layers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake until hot at 375°.

title: potatoes on the grill
directions: From a roll of heavy-duty aluminum foil, tear off approximately 24 to 36-inches.
Leaving the foil in one piece, place half on a flat surface, with the other half away from the working area. Spray the foil on the flat surface with the cooking spray.
Wash potatoes, removing defects, but do not peel.
Slice in 1/8-inch slices, horizontally.
Place sliced potatoes on the sprayed section of aluminum foil, keeping potatoes away from the edge.
Season with salt, pepper, butter, seasoned salt and onions, if desired.
Mix potatoes to spread the seasonings.
Fold the other half section of foil over the potatoes so it meets on the sides; fold on all 3 open sides to close securely.
Place on a hot grill for approximately 30 minutes.
Try not to peek, as the steam builds up inside and aids the cooking process.

"Package" may be turned once during grilling. To test for doneness, pierce through foil with a long-tine fork. My favorite parts of the "package" are the potatoes that are "extra-done" and stick to the foil.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Stir butter, sugar, nuts, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll batter into 1 inch balls with your hands.
Place balls on cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
After the cookies cool, roll them into more confectioners sugar.

title: michigan pate
directions: Saute livers in butter until tender.
Put into blender with remaining ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Spoon into a small crock and refrigerate overnight.
Spread on crackers.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; set aside.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Add to vegetables, mixing well.
Keeps several days in refrigerator and is best made day before serving.

title: peppery scallops(serves 4)
directions: Preheat broiler.
Rinse scallops with running cold water to remove sand from crevices.
Pat dry with paper towels.
In medium bowl, toss scallops with melted margarine to coat well.
On waxed paper, mix bread crumbs, dried basil, pepper and salt.
Dip one flat side of each scallop into bread crumb mixture.
Place scallops, breaded side up, on rack in broiling pan with broiling pan at closest position to source of heat.
Broil scallops 5 minutes without turning until bread crumbs are opaque.
Serve with lemon slices or wedges.

title: sweet cabbage and noodles
directions: Boil the noodles; drain and put aside.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in skillet. Chop up the cabbage coarsely and put in skillet.
Keep adding small amounts of water and sugar; cook until done. Combine noodles and 1/2 stick butter and mix well.

title: fresh cucumber salad
directions: Peel and cut the cucumbers.
Add salt and let them drain for 20 minutes.
Drain water off and add all the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Excellent for summer picnics.

title: tuna veggie casserole
directions: Cook all veggies and garlic in reserved olive and tuna liquid until cooked through, 10 minutes.

In a 2-quart casserole, layer 2/3 can soup, 1/2 noodles, 1/2 veggies, 2/3 soup, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 parsley, 1/2 noodles, 1/2 veggies, 2/3 soup, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 parsley. Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve with tossed salad and hard rolls.

title: finger jello
directions: Bring water to a boil; add to blended gelatins.
Mix well until dissolved.
Pour into 13 x 9 pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into shapes or squares.
Works well in gelatin Jiggler molds.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Wash, trim and shred zucchini.
Mix zucchini in bowl with all the other ingredients, except Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Spoon the mixture into a greased baking dish.
Beat the 4 eggs and pour over zucchini.
Mix lightly with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until the top is set.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings; 130 calories per serving.

title: m&m krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows on High for 2 minutes in microwave, using a large bowl.
Stir to combine.
Micro for several more seconds if needed to melt completely.
Stir in cereal.
Scrape into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with M&M's and press evenly down. Work quickly so M&M's don't melt (it helps to freeze M&M's first).

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Soft cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread on flour tortillas; roll up.
Chill.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Serves with salsa sauce as a dip.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine egg and 1/4 cup of soup.
Stir in uncooked rice, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 20 small meatballs.
Place in frying pan.
Mix remaining soup with Worcestershire and water.
Pour over meatballs. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir often.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain
and add water to juice to make 1/2 cup.
Add unflavored gelatin to this mixture.
In small pan dissolve cranberry sauce over low heat, when dissolved add 2 cups water to pan.
Add juice mixture and dissolve cherry
jello to hot cranberry mixture.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Five minutes before cake is done, bring margarine, cocoa and milk to boil.
Stir in powdered sugar, pecan halves and vanilla and spread over hot cake.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Cream cheese should be soft, mixed with Miracle Whip.
Add pineapple, sugar and marshmallows.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Smooth into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cherries on top.
Cover with lid or Saran Wrap and place in freezer.
Serve frozen or slightly thawed. Great for summer!

title: stickies
directions: Arrange rolls in greased tube pan. Pour dry butterscotch pudding over rolls. Melt butter and mix with sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Pour over rolls. Cover with foil, then dish cloth. Let set overnight. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Check after 15 minutes. If too brown, cover with foil.

title: quick salisbury steak
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, the beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Shape firmly into 6 patties.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook half of the patties in hot oil until browned on both sides.
Remove and set aside.
Repeat with remaining patties.
Spoon off fat.
Add remaining soup and mushrooms.
Boil.
Return patties to skillet.
Cover and cook 20 minutes on reduced heat.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken and put pieces in large baking dish.
Prepare Stove Top dressing as directions on box.
Put dressing around chicken pieces in dish and pour can of cream of chicken soup over. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder. Add carrots, nuts, vanilla and pineapple. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick chicken bake
directions: Mix together and place in a buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
If you prefer cream of mushroom soup or Cheddar cheese soup, go for it.
Do not be afraid to experiment.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop large spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Blend well. Add dry ingredients; mix well. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, olives, chilies and seasoned salt in bowl; mix well.
Spread thinly on tortillas.
Roll as for jelly rolls; chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
May substitute 1/4 cup chunky picante sauce for 1/4 cup sour cream.
Add minced jalapenos or chopped green onions if desired.
Yield:
64 servings.

title: *barbecued burger mix
directions: Brown meat in small amount of hot fat.
Add onion, green pepper and celery; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes, then cook (boil) until firm, but soft (not mushy).
In a large casserole dish, mix everything, except potatoes.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces.
Put potatoes in last and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Can add onion.)

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix using directions for 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool.
Cut into slices.
Alternate layers of cake, condensed milk, strawberries, whipped topping and pecans on serving plate.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with strawberries.
Yields 15 servings.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Thoroughly grease a loaf pan or use 1 small pan and 5 large muffin tins.
Then sprinkle them with sugar/cinnamon mixture. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar together; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add the vanilla and beat in.
Sift together the flour and baking soda; add 1 cup.
Mix well.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Blend.
Mix in the rest of the flour until all is well blended.
Pour into loaf pan or fill small loaf pan 3/4ths full and the muffin cups 2/3rds.
Bake until golden brown; loaf 45 to 50 minutes, the others 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raspberry sherbet spritzer
directions: Place 1 scoop sherbet in each of 6 parfait glasses.
Pour about 1/4 cup sparkling water over sherbet.
Garnish with raspberries.
Serve immediately.

title: deviled ham and egg sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together with salt, if needed.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in vanilla.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into four greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cooked cheese(for sandwiches)
directions: Mix all in heavy saucepan or skillet and cook slowly until melted. Pour in bowl to set.
Use in sandwiches.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Place rice in large casserole dish.
Cut margarine over rice. Spoon soup over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup on top and add water; mix evenly.
Place seasoned chicken pieces on top and bake, uncovered, at 325° until tender (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours), less for boned breasts.
Turn chicken, if necessary, for browning.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crawfish) in large pot; bring to a boil. Add crawfish and cook for about 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except the eggs, for 8 minutes. Strain and pour over eggs.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Put croutons in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Spread with cheese.
Cook and drain sausage and spread over cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/4 hours. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: impossible cherry pie
directions: Grease pie plate (9-inch).
Beat all ingredients except pie filling until smooth.
One minute with hand mixer on high.
Pour into pie pan.
Spoon pie filling on top evenly.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Add 3/4 cup flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle batter with chopped nuts.
Bake at 370° for 15 minutes (in jelly roll pan).
Loosen sides and turn upside down onto a powdered sugar towel.
Roll cake with towel in a jelly roll fashion (roll long way).
Cool for 1 hour.
Unroll and fill with filling.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Place kraut in strainer over bowl.
Drain juice into bowl, squeezing kraut dry.
Add sugar to juice.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, brown sugar and syrup.
Pour melted butter over mixture and stir together until well mixed.
Add 1/4 cup peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt the chocolate and butterscotch chips over hot water.
Add 2/3 cup peanut butter and peanuts.
Spread on top of bars.
Cool and cut.

title: holiday congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate until set.

title: mother's blueberry cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream shortening; add sugar and cream well.
Add beaten eggs.
Add milk and vanilla; set aside.
Dust blueberries in flour.
Mix dry ingredients into sugar/egg mixture, then gently fold in the berries.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
As soon as you remove from oven, sprinkle with sugar; serve warm.

title: lasagna
directions: Steam or brown hamburger meat; drain and mix in sauce and seasoning.
Layer meat, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until noodles are tender.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture becomes thick (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into freezer can of a 1-gallon freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Turn churn off.
Cover with thick towel and let set 1 hour.
Yield: 1 gallon.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put cream cheese in mixer and cream.
Add mayonnaise.
Then add shrimp and other ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight. Serve with chips or vegetable tray.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fun pizza
directions: You will need 1 baking sheet and a rolling pin.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil square with onion; drain well.
Add cheese, cut in small pieces, salt, pepper, 1 cup toasted bread crumbs (about 3 slices of toast), milk, beaten eggs and oleo.
Pour into dish after mixing well.
Top with 2 slices of toast, crumbled up.
Add pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pull walnut size chunks of dough; roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Drop in lightly buttered cake pan into which nuts have been sprinkled.
Let rise.
Bring sugar, cream and butter to a boil.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix water and yeast until yeast is dissolved.
Add your 6 cups of flour and mix up.
Add your salt, oil, honey and rest of the flour.
Knead your dough for 5 minutes. Let rest, covered with a towel, until double in size.
I get 4 loaves of bread and a large size of cinnamon rolls out of this recipe.
You'll also need a very large bowl for the dough.
Bake bread 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: mighty minestrone
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover; drain.
Add stock, garlic and onion.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and zucchini; simmer 30 minutes longer.
Add tomatoes and macaroni; simmer 10 minutes more.
Serve in bowls or mugs.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cheese.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in double boiler.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Add corn flakes; mix gently until coated with green mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper in shape of holly leaves.
Decorate with red hot candies.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: kool-aid slush
directions: Put in freezer in large container.
Stir every hour.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch squares.
In a large skillet, brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add gravy mix and water; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Return meat to skillet.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot noodles or with mashed potatoes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: sandwich buns
directions: Put flour in large mixing bowl.
Make a well in flour, then add the eggs, shortening, sugar, salt and milk.
Put yeast in little bowl with 1/2 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Pour into bowl and mix together.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and form into balls, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Dip in flour and place on greased cookie sheet and press down.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make into 6 balls.
Put 1 big apple, cut in half, on dough before you close up the dough.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on apples.
Roll up; top with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until good and brown.

title: won ton's
directions: Combine hamburger with seasonings.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of hamburger mixture on won ton skin.
Wrap skin around hamburger ball.
Deep fry at medium-high heat until golden brown.
Remove from fryer and serve.
Makes 30.

title: peach pie (2)
directions: Mix ingredients together just to coat fruit, let stand 15 minutes.
Fill pastry lined 9 inch pie pan with fruit mixture, dot with 1 Tbsp. butter.
Cover pie with top crust, seal & flute edges.
Cut several slits to permit steam to escape.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until juices form bubbles that burst slowly and top is golden brown.

title: cream puffs or eclairs
directions: In saucepan, bring water, oleo and sugar to full rolling boil. Add flour all at once, stirring vigorously with wooden spoon and cook about 1 minute or until mixture forms thick smooth ball that leaves sides of saucepan clean.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time, beating vigorously after each.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms in salted water 5 to 8 minutes. Drain.
Mix other ingredients and add.

title: lasagne #1
directions: In shallow baking dish, place enough sauce to cover bottom, then half the noodles.
Spread with cottage cheese, thin slices of Mozzarella, half of remaining sauce, rest of noodles, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides and place as bottom layer in large baking dish. Peel and slice potatoes. Place potatoes over chops. Place peas over top of potatoes, then pour tomato sauce over everything. Cover with foil and bake at 400 degrees for 1 hour. This is a one dish meal and is delicious.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Add water; cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on High
or until tender-crisp.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and onion.
Spoon this
on
top
of	cauliflower.
Sprinkle	with cheese. Microwave
for
1/2 minutes on Medium-high to melt the cheese. Let stand for 2 minutes before serving.

title: easy cheeseball
directions: Mix ham, cream cheese and dressing well.
Roll into ball over pecan pieces.
Cool in refrigerator.
Serve with wheat crackers (Sociables).

title: crackle
directions: Put butter in a nonstick saucepan to liquefy on low/medium heat.
Add brown sugar and constantly stir until it thickens and caramelizes.
Bring to a boil, then let it sit for 5 minutes NOT stirring.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Next, line with saltine crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake at 400° until mixture bubbles.
Spread mixture evenly over crackers. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Put cookie sheet back in the oven until chocolate melts, then remove and smooth chips out.
Put in the refrigerator until mixture hardens and cools.
Break it out of the pan and store in container that is NOT airtight.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake
mix,
sour
cream and eggs in large bowl. Mix. Bring
water
and margarine to a boil in a saucepan. Stir hot mixture
into cake mixture until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan
that
has been greased and floured.
(Do not wash bowl and saucepan.) Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: angel hash salad
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and pineapple juice; blend well. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add egg yolks; blend well.
Return to heat and cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in rest of ingredients, except bananas. Chill overnight.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: tex-mex chicken bites(microwave)
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish, place poultry; cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap and turn back one corner to vent.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Turn poultry pieces over and rearrange by moving the outside pieces to the center of dish.
Cook, covered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes more or until poultry is tender and no longer pink.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: Cook squash
or
zucchini in water with onions for 5 or 10 minutes; drain water off. Save squash and onions.
Combine soup, sour
cream
and
carrots.	Fold
in squash and onions. Pour
in medium
baking dish.
Mix dressing with melted oleo. Spread this on	top
of
squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated steak
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator, turning steak at least once.
Grill to your taste.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan, cook pudding as directed on package. Thoroughly blend dry cake mix into hot pudding.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts if desired.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange bread, sausage and cheese (2 layers of each).
Beat rest of ingredients together and pour over casserole.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight (8 hours).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and sprinkle with paprika and Parmesan cheese and broil until lightly brown.

title: barbara's zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini over small amount of salted water (veggie steaming basket works best) until tender.
In a bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt, cayenne, baking powder, flour and parsley.
Mix and remove lumps, then add chiles, pimento and 1/2 pound grated cheese; stir well.
Add steamed zucchini (well drained) and stir gently.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables with coarse blade and mix together.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in clean jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: hermits
directions: Cream together the sugar and oil.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix milk and molasses and add to sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Fold in raisins.
Blend this mixture with dry ingredients; spread on cookie sheet (mixture will be thick).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cut into squares.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and sugar in bowl.
Add butter.
Blend with pastry blender until consistency of corn meal.
With fork, stir in eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well. Wrap in foil; refrigerate 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease sheets.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Bake 7 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Let margarine melt in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour soups in with margarine.
Add to this 1 cup long grain rice and top with mushrooms.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° (uncovered).
Let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: eggs el dorado
directions: Slice eggs on cutting board with egg slicer or small knife. Melt margarine in skillet. Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender (onion will lose its very white color). Spoon Cheez Whiz into skillet with metal spoon. Add sliced eggs and cook over low heat, stirring often with wooden spoon until cheese is melted. Toast muffin halves in toaster and place on serving plate. Spoon sauce over muffins. Serve immediately.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add all ingredients to warm water.
Sift 6 cups flour; add to mixture, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Pour dough on floured board. Knead well.
Pinch off small balls; make into biscuit size and bake.

title: cheesy pita pizza(low-fat)
directions: Lightly brush bread with 1 tablespoon of the dressing.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Brush bread with half of remaining dressing. Top with Kraft Free singles and pizza toppings.
Drizzle with remaining dressing.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes, or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut into 6 wedges.
Makes 2 servings.
Each serving contains only 1 gram of fat.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes, then add peanut butter, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Stir and drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: sakana no miso yaki(broiled fish with soybean paste)
directions: Combine miso, sake, ginger and sugar.
Mix well.
Soak fish in miso sauce overnight.
Broil until cooked.

title: delicious potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 10 x 10-inch glass or Corning Ware dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until slightly browned and bubbly.
Very quick and easy to prepare!

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Simmer the first 9 ingredients 20 minutes. Add the shrimp and rice.
Serves 4.

title: salmon dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, catsup and horseradish until well mixed.
Fold in salmon and mix well.
Serve with snack crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: vinegar and oil marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Good as a seafood marinade.

title: cream cheese crescent danish
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread 1/2 of crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish. Spread the cream cheese mixture on the crescent rolls.
Place the other 4 crescent rolls on top of the cream cheese mixture.
Pour melted margarine on top and sprinkle with the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tarragon green beans
directions: Cook green beans in a large saucepan of boiling water for 5 minutes or until crisp yet tender.	Drain well.
Return beans to saucepan and add remaining ingredients, tossing well.
Serve immediately.

title: dobosh torte
directions: Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Slowly add sugar.
