Add vanilla and lemon (orange) extract.
Add flour and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites in egg yolk mixture.
Evenly spread 2 to 3 tablespoons of batter on round buttered cake pan.
Bake at 375° to 400° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Continue for all of batter.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops.
Slice 2 or 3 layers of potatoes in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread diced onion on top of potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Then place chops on potatoes.
Mix 2 soups together in bowl and pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Can be turned down to 250° the last 1/2 hour.
Cook until potatoes are tender with fork.
Serve with salad or slaw.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together. Melt margarine and cheese. Mix both mixtures together, with nuts.

title: biscuit muffins
directions: Mix and bake at 450° to 475° for 15 minutes in a greased muffin pan.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Make your favorite dough recipe. Roll dough out and spread 1 pound sausage over dough. Roll up and slice. Bake in oven at 375° for about 50 minutes, making sure sausage is done and well browned. Makes about 50 pinwheels.

title: eggs for a crowd
directions: Blend milk, eggs and spices.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer 7
to
8 slices bread.
Cover with 3 cups of cheese and half
the egg
mixture.
Repeat using balance of ingredients. Refrigerate overnight
or
all day.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let
set
for
a few minutes.
Cut into squares.
Perfect for brunch
or after-dance
breakfast.
Serve
with ham, sausage, melon balls, etc. or sweet rolls, if desired. Serves 12 to 15.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine rice with beef, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Mix lightly.
Shape mixture into 18 balls and place in skillet.
Add sugar to remaining 2 cups tomato juice.
Pour over meatballs in skillet.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes, basting occasionally or until done.

title: hot squash casserole
directions: Saute squash, green pepper and onion in oil until tender, but do not brown.
Add jalapeno peppers and place in buttered 3-quart dish.
Spread soup over top and sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into tube or Bundt pan that has been greased and floured and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: easy cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well over low heat until thoroughly melted together and serve with pork rinds.
Try some cream cheese with this dip.
It adds a great taste.
You won't believe how good it is and it is very low in carbs!

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into 1 inch balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. While warm, roll in powdered sugar and again when cooled.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and onion and cook, stirring after 5 minutes, or until onions are tender.
Stir in mushroom soup and remaining ingredients, stirring often.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
Yield: 8 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Add nuts or raisins or both.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: old fashioned bean soup
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Saute carrots, onion and celery to a golden color in Dutch oven.
Brown ground beef and drain.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Marinate chicken in sherry for 2 to 3 hours.
Pat dry with a paper towel.
Combine breadcrumbs, salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic and 1/4 cup of the almonds.
Dip chicken in butter and roll in breadcrumbs mixture.
Arrange in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with remaining almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Put this mixture in a 10 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing.
Place over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans in large mixing bowl.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter in chafing dish.
Blend in flour, gradually stir in cream.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir small amount of sauce into egg yolks.
Return egg mixture to dish and cook until thick, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Add sherry and lemon juice. Serve as desired, on pastry shells or toast or over rice or with Chinese noodles.
Crab or lobster may be substituted for shrimp.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook all together until thick. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: four-layer delight
directions: Combine flour, softened margarine and 1/2 cup pecans in bowl; mix well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cream confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup whipped topping in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Spread over chilled layer.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Prepare pudding mix using package directions, reducing milk to 3 cups.
Spread over creamed layer.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Spread with mixture of remaining 1 cup whipped topping and 1/2 cup pecans.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken and cut in small pieces.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and paprika.
Use bread crumbs and paprika for topping.
Dot top with butter.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 375° until light brown and bubbly.

title: aggie salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill until set.

title: company casserole
directions: Simmer browned beef and tomato sauce together.
Combine all remaining ingredients (except noodles).
For bottom layer, use half the noodles.
For second layer, use half the noodles mixed with cheese mixture.
For top layer, use meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Reheat at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt the butter and add the pretzels and sugar.
Let the pretzels soak up the margarine, then pat into the bottom of your pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Set aside and let cool.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Chop and combine vegetables, seasonings and vinegar.
Let stand.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; then add cold water. Chill until thickened; then add vegetables.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix altogether, form into balls and drop into hot oil.

title: johnny's favorite lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly in oil; drain.
Add next 8 ingredients. Simmer uncovered about one hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook, drain and rinse noodles.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 noodles in 9 x 13 pan, spread 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 mozzarella cheese, sliced thin, and 1/2 meat mixture. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350 - 375 degrees about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 - 15 minutes before cutting.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour, spices, salt, soda and sugar.
Stir in oil and beaten eggs, then milk.
Add prunes, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pour sauce over cake when taken from the oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch buttered dish or pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown and firm.
Serves 6.

title: egg rolls
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until just done.
Drain and mix in parsley.
Separate egg rolls.
Put little mixture of hamburger then cheese.
Roll and fry in skillet.
Drain really well.
Stand on end to drain.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
When cooled to lukewarm, add yeast and beaten eggs.
Add flour.
Let rise twice and shape into 2 loaves or rolls.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes until tops are brown.

title: tina's dump cake
directions: Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish the cherries (with juice), chocolate morsels and cake mix.
Slice the 2 sticks butter and place them on top of cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix together and pour in casserole dish covered with buttered crackers.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 20 minute pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl; mix for 20 minutes.
Put in ungreased tube pan and put in a cold oven.
Turn heat to 350°; bake for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until half done.
Add chopped onion.
When onion is slightly browned, pour off most of grease; add beans, brown sugar, vinegar and catsup and stir well.
Cover and simmer in oven two hours.

title: basic granola
directions: Combine oats, rye flour, whole-wheat flour and coconut in a large mixing bowl.
Combine honey, salt, water and vanilla in a quart jar.
Cover and shake.
Then add to first mixture.
Stir until evenly moistened.
Divide evenly into two 9 x 13-inch pans. Bake at 350° until desired texture is achieved.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Keeps well in airtight container.
To serve, add raisins, fresh fruit, nuts, etc.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, half the nuts, onion and salt. Form into ball.
Roll ball in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: toughies
directions: Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Bake in rectangular pan.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate angel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, mixing cocoa with dry ingredients.
Spoon batter evenly into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven as directed on the package; let cool.
When cake is completely cooled, carefully remove from pan. Cut in half horizontally.
Place one half, cut side up, on serving plate.
Spread with 3/4 cup fudge topping.
Do not heat topping. Cover with 1 cup whipped topping, then half the cherry pie filling. Place the second half of the cake over cherries, cut side down. Spread with 3/4 cup fudge topping.
Cover with remaining 1 cup whipped topping and remaining cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Just before serving, warm remaining 2 tablespoons fudge topping and drizzle over cherry pie filling.
Makes 12 servings.

title: smooth and creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk in a bowl. Beat slowly at lowest speed of an electric mixer until blended (1 minute).
Fold in whipped topping. Spread on cake at once.
Makes about 4 cups or enough for two 9-inch layers or an angel food cake.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer each of the ingredients in a casserole or crock-pot. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or high in crock-pot 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Mix next three ingredients and place on top.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine first 7 ingredients and toss lightly.
Combine soup and chopped eggs; pour over ingredients.
Top with additional potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes.
To keep fingers from getting greasy, crush potato chips in bag, pour 2/3 in first mixture and sprinkle remainder over the top.

title: cherry torte
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Slowly add sugar, beating well; add vanilla.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip and put layer of whole graham crackers in bottom of pan.
Spread 1/2 mixture on graham crackers. Add another layer of graham crackers then spread with other 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Top with whole can of cherry pie filling, blueberry or apple.
Cherry is the best.

title: humus tahine dip
directions: Boil peas in juice from can til soft (approx. 45 minutes). Let cool and drain.
Add peas to blender and blend until paste like consistency.
Add Sesame Tahine oil (mixed well before adding to peas).
Add garlic, lemon juice and salt.
Blend well. Sprinkle paprika on top.
This is very good on pocket bread, celery or carrots.

title: date balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter, dates, nuts and egg in a 5-quart pot.
Cook on High heat until butter and dates are melted, then cook 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.
After 10 minutes, remove from heat and add vanilla and Rice Krispies; mix well.
When completely mixed, pour mixture onto a plate.
With a spoon scoop out mixture and form small balls.
Place on cookie sheet until all mixture is formed into small balls, then drop balls into a bag with powdered sugar. Shake and remove.
Enjoy.

title: florentine chicken
directions: Saute chicken breast fillets until lightly browned.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Meanwhile, divide spinach in 4 equal portions and arrange a bed of spinach in small broiler-proof casseroles.
Top each portion with a chicken fillet, 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce, 1/4 of the mushrooms and a slice of cheese.
Broil until bubbly and browned.

title: cecile's infamous pork barbecue
directions: Season pork with pepper and place in a crock pot. Cook on low for 8-10 hours. Remove pork from crock pot and remove any bones and fat. Shred pork with a fork and place into a large bowl. Mix equal parts of the 2 barbecue sauces together and mix with shredded pork to moisten well. The barbecue can be served immediately but is best if refrigerated overnight to let the meat absorb the sauce. Reheat in microwave or crockpot. Freezes well.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Blend all dry ingredients and stir in.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Top with 3 cups of buttered cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hearty bean soup
directions: Cook bacon in large heavy saucepan until crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Leave a small amount of drippings in pan (about 1 tablespoon).
Add onion, carrot and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes which have been mashed or cut into small pieces.
Stir in navy beans along with salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Add crumbled bacon and parsley flakes.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve in warmed soup bowls.

title: creamy economical eggnog
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process at Liquefy until smooth.
Pour into cups and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: beery beef stew
directions: Coat cubed meat in flour with salt and pepper; set aside.
In a large pot, heat 1/4 cup olive oil and saute onion and garlic until soft, 5 minutes.
Remove onions from pot; add rest of olive oil and heat.
Add the floured meat, browning it well on all sides.
Return onion mixture to meat, the beer, 3 sauces and herbs.
Mix well and bring mixture to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour boiling water over soda and dates; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Cream sugar and oleo; add egg.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Then add nuts and date mixture. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350°.
When cake is done, pour the icing over cake and return to oven until brown and bubbly.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put in bread pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in lukewarm water, then add 1/2 cup flour and make batter.
Let rise 1/2 hour in warm place. Then beat egg and shortening and add to ingredients.
Add remaining flour.
Spoon batter into muffin pan.
Let rise 30 minutes and bake at 400°.
Batter should be thickness of cake dough.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Make the hamburger into small balls and put in soup.
Boil all ingredients, except noodles, on medium low for 30 minutes.
Add the noodles.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
If to thick, add more water or tomato juice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayo, sugar, onion and vinegar for dressing.
Fry bacon crisp and crunch up in salad.
Add raisins. Let set 1 hour before serving.

title: apple-walnut cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, the cinnamon and 1/2 cup walnuts.
Place apples in bottom of a greased 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and butter; add dry ingredients, all at once, and mix until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until center is done.
Cut in wedges. Serve with cinnamon-topped whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter until moistened.
Melt butter in skillet.
Drop mixture in hot buttered skillet by spoonfuls (as in pancakes).
Brown on both sides.
Makes 8 patties.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Press mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Take several potatoes and wash well. Rub each one with olive oil, then place them on a cookie sheet. Sprinkle side up with salt and bake for 30 minutes, then flip the potatoes over, salt again and poke a few holes in them.
Cook for 30 more minutes . . . and voila!
I even eat the skin!

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: This is an old recipe that has been handed down for generations.
It is a true recipe for making hominy.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° to 350°, uncovered.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots; put in bowl and put all the ingredients over carrots.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients in order in recipe, except butter.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Good hot or cold.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder; set aside. Combine egg, milk, melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and spread out in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Drain peaches reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Chop peaches and put on top of batter.
Beat together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach liquid reserve.
Pour on top of peaches in pan.
Combine the 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: mama myrtle colvin's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time alternately with 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and salt, blending well.
Bake at 300° in greased and floured loaf pan, about 45 minutes.

title: caramel-filled chocolate cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In large bowl, beat 1 cup sugar, brown sugar and butter until fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
With floured hands, shape about 1 tablespoon of dough around 1 Rolo caramel candy, for each cookie.
In small bowl, combine nuts and sugar.
Press one side of cookie in mixture. Place this side up and bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Drizzle melted white chocolate over cookies.

title: italian chicken
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with butter.
Place boneless chicken breasts in greased pan.
Slice up onion, mushrooms and tomato and place on top.
Cover thoroughly with a small bottle of Italian dressing.
Sprinkle on garlic salt.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; cool.
Add onions, celery, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Cut
bacon
into small pieces; fry to crisp. Remove from grease.
Add
flour
to grease; stir until smooth. Do not let brown.
Add vinegar and water.
Bring to boil;
let thicken.
Pour over potatoes.
Add
bacon and mix well.
Serve warm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken and celery soup and chicken broth.
Heat and stir until smooth; add Veg-All.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Add water chestnuts and the chicken.

title: corn and shrimp soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine (approximately 1/2 stick) until soft.
Add shrimp (if fresh) until pink.
Add all other ingredients and cook slowly for 3 hours.
This soup freezes well.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Streusel Mixture:
Mix by hand all ingredients until they form a crumbly mixture.
Set aside.

title: lasting friendship
directions: Add first 4 ingredients, mix well with a good conscience. Pour into a deserving heart and bake in Christian surroundings until tender and not apt to fall apart.
Serve warm, topped with 1 cup laughter and a heaping tablespoonful of caution.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Place pie filling in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with pineapple.
Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: chicken
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all this with 3/4 bottle Italian salad dressing.
Marinate overnight.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Have braunschweiger soft and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers or party rye.

title: microwavable green beans with bacon
directions: Mix margarine, soy sauce, onion, garlic and beans in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: billie's homemade hotdog "coney" sauce
directions: Place all ingredients into sauce pan together and simmer slowly.
To thicken, stir frequently.

title: lepkuchen
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add spices with flour.
Add the soda in warm water.
Add lemon.
When mixed, add nuts, dates and raisins.
Spread in a greased shallow pan and bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut when warm.
Frost when cool.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs and stir in milk, flour and all other ingredients. Drop from spoon in deep fat.
Fry until brown.
Serves 6 to 8. Serve with plenty of butter and syrup!

title: overnight refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat the eggs and add eggs, sugar and salt to the yeast mixture.
Add melted shortening.
(I prefer to use butter for the taste.)
Add 2 cups of flour.
Mix until smooth and add the rest of the flour.
Mix well and put into a greased bowl.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together until creamy and nongrainy, then add 2 cups plus 4 tablespoons sifted flour.
Mix and add 12 ounce bag semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, pepper and onion in pan. Cook until meat is browned.
Drain well.
Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain.
Add soup and macaroni to beef.
Add milk and catsup.
Mix well.
Fold in cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: mark's vegetarian enchiladas
directions: Saute onion, zucchini and pepper in oil until soft.
Place in a bowl with drained kidney beans and peanuts.
Mix. Wrap filling and a little Cheddar cheese in tortilla.
Place in baking dish.
Repeat with the rest of tortillas.
Top with Cheddar cheese and chopped tomato.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and tortillas are heated through.
Serve with plain yogurt.

title: easy scrambled eggs
directions: Break eggs into blender, add soup and blend.

title: peanut butter fudge(children won't pass up this fudge.)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
In a saucepan, heat the sugar and milk to a soft ball stage.
(Use a candy thermometer.) Pour over peanut butter mixture and stir until well mixed.
Spread in a greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool, then cut into squares.
Makes 64 one-inch squares.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix together and let stand several hours in refrigerator.

title: fettuccine noodles with cheese sauce
directions: Cook noodles until tender. Stir in cheese, onion, black pepper, oregano, chives and salt. Serve warm.

title: vegetable soup
directions: *Instant barley works, but does not taste as good.
Boil less time for quick.

title: parmesan bread spread
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix cheese, margarine and Italian seasoning.
Spread on bread.
Place bread slices on a cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: banana bread
directions: * Do not use self-rising flour in this recipe.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Add sugar, chocolate and milk.
Cook on top of stove for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
When cool, then beat.
Spread over cool cake.

title: nut bonbon cookies
directions: Mix together with a fork the cream cheese and butter or margarine.
Mix flour in well with hands. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: garlic lime chicken
directions: Mix together soy sauce, lime juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and mustard.
Place chicken in bowl and pour sauce over it. Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Spray a nonstick pan with Pam and place on a burner set at medium heat. Add chicken and cook about 6 minutes on each side or until meat is fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings, 130 calories each.

title: christmas steamed pecan cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl; add egg yolks and beat well.
In separate bowl, combine pecans and raisins and mix in about 1 cup of flour to coat.
Add baking powder and salt to remaining flour.
Gradually add flour to creamed sugars, butter and egg mixture, a cup at a time.
Alternate with lemon extract until all flour and extract have been used.
Then mix in pecans and raisins; stir well.
(May take two mixing bowls to mix properly.) Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter mixture.

title: peanut puffs
directions: Heat butter in 3 quart saucepan over low heat until melted. Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and peanuts until well coated.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand at room temperature until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes 2 dozen puffs (24 servings).

title: mandarin salad(this recipe is ideal for potlucks or large groups of people)
directions: Put fruit and coconut in a large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over fruit and blend.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows. Stir well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Garnish with mint or maraschino cherries.
Serves 10 to 20.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apples, apple juice concentrate, thickener and spice.
Stir until apples are well coated.
Add lemon juice, if desired, to keep apples light colored.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan and top with other crust or use pastry strips.
Seal the edges and cut slits in top of crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
This recipe is great for people who cannot have sugar.
For diabetics, the exchange is 1 1/2 fruit, 1 bread and 2 fats.
The calorie count is 220.

title: chess squares
directions: You will also need one 13 x 9-inch pan or dish.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, cilantro, onion and peppers (remove seeds fo a milder taste).
Add lemon juice and salt to taste.
Make ahead, will mellow with time.
Goes great with Margaritas in the summertime.

title: diabetic beef burgundy
directions: Brown beef in hot frypan.
Add salt, pepper, bay leaf, thyme and 1 1/2 cups water.
Simmer, covered, about 1 3/4 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onion.
Simmer, covered, until tender, about 20 minutes.
Mix flour with 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Add slowly to meat mixture, stirring, gently. Cook until thickened.
Garnish with parsley.

title: mexican enchiladas
directions: Chop onion.
In separate bowls, grate cheeses.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup and olives.
Salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Empty enchilada sauce into shallow dish.
Melt shortening and fry tortillas until soft.
Dip tortillas into enchilada sauce and place in baking dish.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture, onion and Jack cheese.
Fold, packing side by side.
Pour remainder of enchilada sauce over folded enchiladas and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Can be frozen.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and cool. Mix all ingredients together. You may also add mustard if you like.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Butter pan thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and core apples; do not peel. Cook until tender.

Let stand until cool. Put apples through a food mill or colander and measure 1 cup fruit to 1 cup sugar. Cook 7 cups at a time. Add the nutmeg and cinnamon. Cook slowly for 1 hour, stirring often to keep from scorching. Test for doneness by putting 1 tablespoon apples in a dish and cool completely.
If thickened, pour into hot jars and seal.
Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: mayonnaise cornbread muffins
directions: Grease 12 (2 1/2 x 1 1/4 inch) muffin cups.
Stir together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Stir milk into mayonnaise in another small bowl.
Stir milk mixture into flour mixture just until moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy). Turn into prepared pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden; or bake in greased iron skillet in the oven at 400° for 25-30 minutes.

title: to make eagle brand milk
directions: Melt margarine in boiling water.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix in a blender until thick.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Mix ingredients and mold, making a well in the center.
At serving time, fill center with cocktail sauce. Serve with crackers.
Serves 8 to 10 guests.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, molasses and egg together thoroughly. Sift flour, baking soda and ginger and/or cinnamon.
Stir gradually into the shortening mixture.
Roll into small balls with hands.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Grease and lightly flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan (do not use smaller).
In separate bowl, cream the cream cheese, oleo and sugar.
Set aside.
Sprinkle all coconut on bottom of greased pan.
Set aside.
Pour cake mix over coconut and nuts.
With teaspoon, dollop cream cheese mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cream cheese will sink into cake as it bakes causing the cake to crack.
Looks like a disaster, tastes like nuthin you've ever tasted.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Add
milk
to
egg.
Stir in instant onion and Cream of Wheat; let
stand
while	mixing	together tuna, lemon juice, salt, pepper
and peas.
Combine with Cream of Wheat mixture. Pour
into greased loaf pan.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with cream sauce.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: christmas candle loaves
directions: Preheat electric oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda into bowl. Stir in nuts, milk and oatmeal.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir only until blended.
Do not overbeat.
Some lumps should remain.
Pour into 6 greased 6 ounce frozen juice cans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from cans. Cool thoroughly. Wrap cooled bread.
Store one day for easy slicing or freeze for later use.
Spread top of each loaf with thin confectioners sugar frosting allowing some frosting to drip down sides.
Top with red and green candied fruit.
Makes 6 small loaves.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Chop cheese, corned beef and onion.
Cook macaroni and drain. Add to cheese and corned beef.
Mix milk and soup; add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Peppers may be added for color.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and vanilla.
Pour into Bundt pan sprayed with Pam and sprinkled with granulated sugar.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Sprinkle sifted powdered sugar on top.

title: skillet beef and noodles
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; cover.
Simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until noodles are tender.

title: marshmallow krispie bars
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Grease
bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare
and bake brownies, following package directions for original recipe.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle marshmallows on hot brownies.
Return to oven.
Bake 3 minutes longer.

title: pot pie casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken or other meat, soup, vegetables and seasoning in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Stir baking mix and milk until blended.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 30 minutes or until crust is light golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: deviled chicken wings
directions: Mix butter and mustard.
Brush over seasoned chicken.
Bake at 400 degrees for about 20 minutes, basting occasionally until crisp and golden.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni beef stew
directions: Boil stew meat, onion, celery, bell pepper, garlic powder in water until tender.
Add tomato sauce, beef broth, and salt and pepper.
Cook until done.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add the rest.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour (a little at a time).
Add flavoring.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into greased spring-form pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.

title: mexican wedding rings
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream butter or margarine and confectioners sugar.
Mix the 2 mixtures together.
Blend in vanilla and almond extracts and the nuts.
Form into very small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 25 minutes at 325° or until lightly browned.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm. When they are entirely cool, roll again in confectioners sugar. This second rolling makes a prettier cookie.

title: margaret hanson's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender; drain well, then mash.
Saute chopped onions in butter.
Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Put in casserole dish; top with cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy oven fries
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into 8 wedges.
Combine cheese and next 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Dip potatoes in butter and arrange on lightly greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese mixture on potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes until brown.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Mix in oatmeal and nuts and chocolate chips.
Mold into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: chocolate dotted cake(children love this cake.)
directions: In a bowl, beat shortening, sugar, vanilla, water and eggs until mixture is light and fluffy.
In a separate dish, mix flour with baking soda and salt, then blend into shortening mixture. Stir in nuts and chips.
Bake in a lightly greased Bundt pan in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn and nuts in large baking pan (2 1/2-inches deep). I use aluminum throw away-bake turkey size.
Spray pan with Pam. Bring to boil the margarine, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and maple flavoring.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat popcorn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool. Store in metal cookie cans.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Mix all but white sugar and butter together.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Top with mixture of white sugar and butter mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: light dinner rolls
directions: Heat
milk,
water
and
butter
in saucepan until very warm. Combine
cups
flour,
sugar,
salt and dry yeast in mixing bowl.
(If
you
use
wet
yeast
soak in 1/3 cup warm water.) Add
heated
mixture
and egg.
Beat at high speed of electric mixer
2 minutes.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board and cover with a bowl.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.
Shape into a ball, place in greased bowl. Turn
once
to grease
top.
Cover and let rise in warm place free
from
draft about
minutes or until double in bulk. Grease
2 large baking sheets.
Spoon out dough and shape into balls
as
desired
(about 1
1/2 to 2 inch rolls).
Place on sheets.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, debone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli according to package instructions.
In large bowl, mix chicken, broccoli, soup and sour cream.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch oblong dish.
Sprinkle crackers over and pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Sprinkle poppy seed over.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger meat with onion.
Roll hamburger mixture, beans and cheese in tortilla shells.
It takes about a tablespoon each of the hamburger mixture, beans and cheese to each shell.
Mix 1/2 can water with enchilada sauce; place enchiladas in baking pan, seam side down.
Pour sauce over enchiladas and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400° until heated through and cheese melts.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put rice, onion soup, mushrooms, water and margarine in casserole dish.
Stir well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Stir and bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil over medium heat. Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add the Jell-O.
Cool. Wash the raspberries in ice water and drain. Fill the shells.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Refrigerate. Cover with Cool Whip and decorate with fresh raspberries.

title: yellow cucumber pickle
directions: Peel cucumbers. Slice lengthwise or across.
Take out seeds. Soak in lime water for 24 hours. Drain off lime water and wash real good, 2 or 3 times. Soak in cold ice water for 3 hours. Drain off the ice water real good.

title: mexican corn bread-in-a-meal
directions: Brown meat with onions and peppers.
Mix cornmeal, salt, soda, milk, corn and eggs.
Grease large cast-iron skillet with drippings.
Heat skillet, then pour 1/2 of cornmeal mixture to cover bottom of skillet.
Add meat mixture, cover that with cheese, then rest of corn bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: good morning cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Drop by teaspoonful about 2 1/2-inches apart.
Flatten a little.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked shell.
Bake at 325°
until golden brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1 cup cold water; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring 1 cup of water to boil.
Add sugar and jello. Bring to boil; remove from stove.
Add gelatin mixture.
Stir and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into greased pan.
Cut into squares.

title: welsh rarebit and kielbasa soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine soup and mustard until blended. Add water, beer and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add kielbasa; lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Before serving, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough on pizza pan for 10 minutes and let it cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spread over cooked dough.
Cut into slices, then add fruit slices and keep refrigerated.

title: thrown together
directions: In
a large skillet, put hamburger, onion, salt and pepper. Fry, breaking up meat as it fries.
Cook.
Add pork and beans, cinnamon, catsup and brown sugar; simmer.
Good on small hamburger buns.

title: texas ranch style beans
directions: Cook beans, pork, onion, garlic, salt and pepper slowly for 2 hours.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, sugar and hot sauce.
Cook slowly for 3 more hours.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; reserve liquid.
Add enough milk for 1 cup. Flake salmon.
Combine all ingredients and pack in greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Combine in large bowl the flour, cornstarch, salt and sugar. Add raspberries and the lemon juice; blend thoroughly.
Turn into pastry lined pan; dot with the butter.
Place top crust over filling; seal and flute.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce oven to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beer cheese
directions: Open and let beer sit over night. Mix everything into a big mixing bowl. Beat until real smooth. Cover and let sit in refrigerator a day or so, then serve.

title: mocha mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 2 to 3 tablespoons to one cup boiling water.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Toast the ramen noodles and the slivered almonds on a cookie sheet for 3 - 4 minutes in a 350 oven.
Add to the slaw and the onions (which have been chopped).
Toss together.
Add the dressing just before serving and mix together with salad.

title: grace's oven baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together

title: apple dipper
directions: Combine cream cheese and apple cider until smooth and creamy. Blend in well grated apple; stir in chives and salt to taste. Chill.
Serve with carrot and celery sticks, radishes, apple wedges or crackers as desired.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Add vegetables, bell pepper and celery and finish browning meat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer at least an hour for best flavor.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots; cut into strips lengthwise.
Cook, uncovered, in boiling salted water until tender.
Place in shallow baking dish. Melt butter, stir in sugar and flour.
Gradually add orange juice and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Pour evenly over carrots. Garnish with orange slices, if desired.

title: eggplant mexicana
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large non-stick skillet and simmer gently, 15 to 20 minutes, or until eggplant is tender. Serve immediately.

title: chicken corn noodle soup
directions: Skin chicken; boil in broth.
Take chicken off bone.
Skim fat from broth.
Add both corns and parsley.

title: easy pizza
directions: Roll out each biscuit very thin.
Place on a cookie sheet (sprayed lightly with Pam).
Spoon sauce over each biscuit.
Add three pepperoni pieces and then add cheese on each biscuit.
Bake at 425° for about 8 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add lemon juice and orange and pineapple juices; boil for 1 minute.
Set aside.
Dice apples; mix all together and chill.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: plum good bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured mini loaf pans (six).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: indian chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 45 to 60 minutes, stirring (OFTEN).
Chill.

title: cabbage and green pea salad
directions: Combine cabbage and uncooked green peas in a bowl. Place nuts in a shallow pan and roast at 300° until lightly browned. Let cool. Combine rest of ingredients and mix into salad. Add nuts just before serving. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Combine pumpkin, bread mix, egg and raisins.
Stir until moist.
Spoon into greased medium muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 30 muffins.
May be frozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each.
Add 2 cups flour, then sour cream.
Add vanilla. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a 10-inch tube cake pan.

title: john's dutch baby
directions: Beat eggs about 1 minute.
Add milk and melted butter; mix well.
Add 1 cup of flour and beat 30 seconds.
Pour batter into a well buttered, ovenproof, 12-inch skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, until batter has risen and edges are golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, cut into wedges and serve immediately.

title: yogurt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: tabouleh(green arabic salad)
directions: Soak the burgul in water for 15-20 minutes or until softened but a little resistant to the bite.
Drain and squeeze out excess moisture.

title: graham cracker cookies(yields 24)
directions: Arrange graham crackers on a buttered cookie sheet that has sides.
Bring butter and sugar to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add nuts and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut between each square and remove.
(Don't use flat cookie sheet as it may run over in your oven!)

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Cover ham hocks with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer until meat is tender and begins to fall off bones.
Take out bones and remove any remaining meat to return to pot.
Add tomato sauce, potatoes, sausage, carrots, onion, celery and macaroni.
Simmer until potatoes and macaroni are almost done.
Add cornstarch to thicken. Season with salt and pepper. Add kidney beans and simmer for 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 hungry adults.

title: mrs. bergstrom's swedish rye bread(swedish name:  vort limpa)
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Knead and let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Knead and shape into 4 oval loaves on 2 jelly roll baking sheets.
Let rise to double in size.
You can knead in 1 cup candied fruit after the first kneading (before you shape into loaves).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well again.
Refrigerate to chill.

title: home baked beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
In a large kettle (night before) cover beans with fresh water and soak overnight.
In the morning, parboil beans in new fresh water with a little salt.
Cook beans on medium heat until soft and whole but not squashy (about 1 hour).
Now you are ready to put beans into baking pot as follows: Cut up onion in small pieces and put in bottom of pot along with the salt pork.
Add the parboiled beans.
(Do not throw away the water used to cook beans.)
Add mustard, ginger, sugar, molasses, vinegar and 1 teaspoon of black pepper.
(No more salt.)
Fill bean pot with par boiling water (water used to cook beans).
Cover beans.
(Save any remaining water to be used during cooking.) Bake in a 300° oven all day.
If in the oven by 10:00 A.M. they should be ready by 5:00 P.M.
Check beans about twice a day, if dry add more water.
Serve with favorite salad and hot dogs.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients.
Combine and add raisins.
Pour into greased loaf pans (3 or 4), depending on size. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm to the touch in the middle of the loaf.
Serve with cream cheese or a cream cheese frosting.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread.
Then add peanuts and cook until peanuts quit popping.
Then add soda and salt.
Stir well. Pour into buttered dish.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: glazed apricot chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix. Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; spread dressing mixture over chicken.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gone-all-afternoon stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large casserole with lid to fit.
Bake for 5 hours in a 275° oven.
Can use more carrots and potatoes if you wish.

title: near pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add milk; mix well.
Add flour and beat until real creamy.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Pour in 10 to 12-cup Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: party macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni.
Chop celery stalks fine and eggs (chop whole eggs fine and mash yolks with mustard).
Combine vinegar, sugar, salad dressing and evaporated milk and add to mixture.
Garnish with carrots and paprika.

title: oreo cookie treat
directions: Mix together cookie crumbs and butter.
Press into oblong dish.
Combine milk and pudding mix, stir in ice cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill to set.
Top with layer of whipped topping.
Crush remaining 1/4 package of Oreos and sprinkle crumbs on top. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Heat butter in skillet large enough to hold chicken. Add chicken, skin-side down. cook 10 minutes until brown on skin side. Turn and cook 5 minutes. Remove and set aside. In skillet, add onion and garlic - cook briefly. Add tarragon and wine. Stir well. Add water. Return chicken to pan; cover. cook 20 minutes. Serve on Rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch or two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes in large pan or 55 to 60 minutes in smaller pans.

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, sugar and margarine. Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth. Stir in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Refrigerate.

title: almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Blanch	almonds
in
water; add baking soda to remove skin.
Put in blender a little at a time to	chop very
fine.
Mix
almonds,	butter	and
sugar
until smooth.
Add extract and baking powder.	Mix flour into batter a little at a time until mixture is easy to work with by hand. Shape into 1 inch balls and flatten into crescent shape.
Bake on cookie sheet until light
brown
on bottom, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool cookies, then coat with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Can be frozen for storage.

title: zippy pepper dip
directions: Chop and mix jalapeno peppers, bell peppers, onions and tomatoes.
Combine salt, sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
Pour over. Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: crispy-crumb eggs
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove.
Add bread crumbs to bacon drippings and heat until crumbs are crisp and brown; remove crumbs.
Add milk and seasonings to eggs; scramble in bacon drippings.
When nearly set, add bacon and crumbs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grape jam - cheesecake cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Slice cookie roll 1/4-inch thick.
Place slices in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cookie dough will be puffy when removed from oven.
Spread with grape jam.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and beat at medium speed.
Pour over jam layer; spread filling to edges.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into dessert squares.

title: new england orange pudding
directions: Combine beaten yolks, both juices and rind.
Add all other ingredients except the whites and beat well.
Finally fold in the beaten whites.
Pour into souffle or other baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: red cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix cocoa and food coloring together.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture and beat.
Add vinegar and soda.
Fold in sifted flour and salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, then roll the mixture into balls and place the balls on a piece of wax paper.

title: party punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Combine pineapple juice and cranberry juice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Float lemon slices and ice ring.
Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Beat eggs and milk together; toss with spaghetti and pour in ungreased dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top of spaghetti.
Add some garlic and oregano to your taste.
Spread pepperoni over top, then mushrooms and finish with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: popcorn peanut bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in medium size bowl.
Heat to full boil in microwave, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Mix popcorn with peanuts.
Pour peanut butter mixture over popcorn and peanuts.
Stir to coat. Pat firmly into 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone chicken and dice into small pieces.
Mix soups and sour cream, then add chicken to the mixture.
Pour and spread into baking dish.
Crumble crackers and mix into melted butter.
Spread over top of melted butter.
Spread over top of chicken and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cookie cutter play dough(do not eat)
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Add oil, water and food coloring or Kool-Aid (Kool-Aid adds color and smell).
Cook for 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from the pan.
Knead.
Store in airtight container.
Just play and have fun!

title: microwave meatball appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange meatballs in single layer in glass baking dish.
Microwave for 4 1/2 minutes.
Turn meatballs over.
Move meatballs from edges to center of baking dish.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes longer or to desired degree of doneness.
Serve hot. Yields 6 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add milk and bananas, then mix in flour, baking powder, soda and salt, then add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cranberry and orange salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water; let cool.
Grind oranges and cranberries.
Add nuts.
Add all ingredients to partially set jello.
Refrigerate.

title: okra tomato gumbo
directions: Fry
bacon
until
crisp;
remove, leaving drippings in Dutch oven. Reserve bacon to add to finished gumbo.
Add round steak slices
and
brown
slowly,
adding onions toward end of process. Add
tomatoes
with
juice, water, chicken stock and bouillon cubes;
simmer
1 hour or more.
Add frozen limas and cook 20 minutes.
Add sliced okra, ham and chicken.
Simmer 20 minutes. Just before serving, add the shrimp and drained corn and
heat thoroughly.
Taste
and adjust seasoning with salt, pepper
and pepper
sauce.
Serve in large shallow bowls with cornbread or cheese biscuits.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Soften cream cheese and separate the egg.
Blend cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Spread 1 roll of crescent dough in 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Pour filling in and then spread the other roll of crescents on top.
Glaze with egg white.
Cook at 350° until filling is done, approximately 1/2 hour.
Cool and then glaze top with confectioners sugar and water mixture.
Top with almonds and refrigerate.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl; add Cool Whip. Fold until blended.
Heap on pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator a least 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 6 generously.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
While butter is melting, mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour this mixture in pan with melted butter.
Spoon peaches on top.
Don't mix them in.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add zucchini and vanilla; mix well. Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks.
Freezes well.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients and press in a cake pan (12 x 9 1/2-inch).
Bake 12 minutes at 370°.
Cool.
Mix together melted chocolate and peanut butter; spread over baked layer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all but berries together in boiler; cook over medium heat until boiled for 1 minute.
Let cool.
Slice 1 pint strawberries; fold into cool mixture.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs and applesauce.
Add onion, celery flakes, mustard, salt, pepper, egg and the ground beef.
Blend thoroughly.
Shape into a round loaf in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
With a spoon, make a depression in top of loaf.

title: taco pasta
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper. Drain then mix hamburger, cream cheese, taco seasoning, mushrooms and pasta sauce. Stuff into shells.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes, crush chips on top and then cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomato and sour cream.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and oil together until sugar dissolves. Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Marinate overnight.

title: mexican crescent bake
directions: Line oblong glass baking dish with unbaked dinner rolls for crust (bring up around edges, too).
Brown ground beef; drain and stir in refried beans and Sloppy Joes mix.
Put meat mixture on unbaked crust.
Mix sour cream, egg and cheese.
Pour sour cream mixture on top of meat.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Simmer on low for 45 minutes.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish with a very tight lid.
Bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.
Do not open lid during baking.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: granola cereal(low-fat)
directions: Combine oatmeal, dry milk, cinnamon and salt in large cake pan. In saucepan, mix brown sugar, applesauce and honey.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour this over dry ingredients in cake pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool; add raisins and store in airtight container.

title: methodist chicken
directions: Put 1 cup of rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay cut-up fryer on top of rice.
Mix together and spoon on top: cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, Lipton onion soup mix, water and chopped pepper, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 350°.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pineapple juice, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and salt; cook over low heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold remaining ingredients into cooked mixture.
Spoon into an 8-inch pan. Freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 8 to 9 servings.

title: little league egg-dipped toast
directions: In a shallow dish, beat the eggs slightly and add the salt, sugar and milk.
Dip the bread slices in the mixture, turning to moisten both sides.
Butter as needed to keep the slices from sticking.
Serve hot.
This is very good with bacon or ham and preserves.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Chop Crisco into flour.
Same with butter if not using buttermilk.
Pour in milk a little at a time.
Mix until it forms into a dough ball (not stiff).
Pat out into flour.
Cut out biscuits.
Bake at 425° until golden brown, about 22 to 25 minutes, on a buttered cookie sheet.

title: mountain blackberry jam
directions: Wash and grind berries or crush completely one layer at a time, so that each berry is reduced to pulp.
Pour sugar into dry dish.
Measure 6 cups berries into a large kettle.
Add pectin. Stir well and bring to a boil.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Continue stirring and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil for 4 minutes. Pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: lime pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and salt.
Place spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Heat mixture to make a syrup.
Soak cucumbers in syrup overnight.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccini according to package directions.
Drain well and place on a warm serving dish large enough for tossing.
Add butter, whipping cream, cheese and parsley; toss until fettuccini is well coated.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese across the bottom of baking pan. Pour the chili over cream cheese. Finally lay slices of cheese over top. Bake in oven at 350 until cheese has melted and chili is hot, approximately 20-30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Put in casserole and add topping mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Dissolve the sugar in vinegar in a saucepan and add the cherries and dill pickles.
Cook for 1 or 2 minutes, then pack in sterilized jars.
Seal the jars, process for 5 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, mustard, onion, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, parsley flakes, salt and pepper in a 1-quart saucepan. Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in crab meat and sherry.
Melt Cheddar cheese (2 to 3 ounces) on top.
Serve while warm with crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown beef or turkey in skillet along with onions, until meat is no longer pink.
Drain.
Make macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
In a 2-quart casserole dish layer the macaroni and cheese, meat and green beans twice, topping with a layer of macaroni and cheese.
Mix the can of cream of mushroom soup with a soup can of milk (you can use nonfat if you choose) and pour over casserole.
You might want to spray the casserole with Pam before starting.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Quick and delicious.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix together with fat-free Ranch dressing.
Add grapes and diced cooked chicken for a main dish meal.

title: mary's swiss steak
directions: Spread flour over the round steak and pound it into the meat. Turn steak over and flour and pound.
Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Brown in a large skillet (electric frying pan works fine).

title: celery relish
directions: Seed and finely chop peppers; combine with celery.
Cover with water and boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until celery is tender.
Pack immediately into sterilized jars and seal.

title: mostaccioli for 40 people
directions: Brown meat, garlic and onion; drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sauce and seasonings.
Add water to desired consistency (sauce thickens as it cooks).
Cook slowly for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peaches 'n' cream pudding cake
directions: Drain peaches, save juice.
Arrange
peaches in oiled 9 x 9-inch or a 7 x 11-inch baking
dish.
Peaches may be sliced thinner, if you desire.
Spread pudding over peaches.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Add
mayonnaise and substitute peach juice for water.
Spread
batter
over
the pudding and peaches.
Bake at 350° (325° if using glass pan) for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.
Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: chicken continental
directions: Chop up an onion in small pieces.
Saute in butter.
Add the rest of the ingredients except for cheese and taco shells.
Stir well.
Butter a casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into dish. Crush up 6 taco shells and sprinkle over mixture.
Top with 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat procedure again: mixture, shells and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in pie filling; spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix onto fruit; spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Dot with butter.
Bake 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: squash casserole supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients but bread crumbs.
Grease baking dish with margarine.
Sprinkle some bread crumbs in bottom of casserole.
Add the combined mixture.
Top with margarine.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Place 1/2 of dough in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) pans.
(Barely cover bottom.)
Spread 1 can of pie filling over the dough.
Spread other half of batter over filling. Sprinkle topping over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (325° for glass dish).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put layer of potatoes, onion and cheese and cover with white sauce until baking bowl is full.

title: aunt lila's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add broth until mixture is slightly thinned.
Put in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Take off lid or foil and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: picaddillo(a favorite in miami's cuban restaurants)
directions: In a large casserole, cook beef in olive oil until browned. Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients, except wine and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add wine and serve over yellow rice.
Flavor improves if stored in the refrigerator overnight.
Add a small amount of water to thin out slightly, if necessary.
Serves 8.

title: creamed dried beef(chipped beef gravy)
directions: Tear dried beef into medium size pieces.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add beef; cook until edges curl.
Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Serve over toast or biscuits.

title: fat man's shrimp
directions: Mix together sour cream, soup, cheese and mustard.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer spinach, shrimp and sauce. Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning, then all the other ingredients.
Do not drain the liquid.
I even add 1 can of water.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with cornbread, crackers or French bread.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil squash; drain.
Saute onion in half of the butter until golden.
Pour into squash all ingredients except eggs (when cool).
Grease casserole.
Saute bread crumbs in butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce walnut cake
directions: Toast walnuts in saucepan over medium heat, shaking pan frequently; chop.
Blend sugar and margarine; add all other ingredients, stirring until all ingredients are well blended. Bake in a greased tube pan 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: layered hamburger bake
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat in skillet, drain.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt, pepper and noodles.
Set aside.
Stir together cream cheese, sour cream, milk and onion.
In 2-quart casserole, layer ground beef-noodle mixture and half of the cream cheese mixture.
Add spinach and remaining ground beef-noodle mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and add remaining cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and melt.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin in a bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Grease 2 loaf pans and flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook the potatoes, then grate or slice the potatoes.
Add all ingredients except paprika.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared and refrigerated overnight.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop teaspoonful amounts on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: freda's chicken crescents
directions: Separate rolls into 8 triangles; spread each with a piece of cooked chicken.
Place sliced mushrooms on each piece, smidgen of chives and pinch of lemon pepper.
Roll up and seal pastry. Dip in melted butter (roll in bread crumbs, optional).
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Place rest of chicken, chives, mushrooms and lemon pepper in broth and heat.
Serve sauce over crispy baked chicken crescents.
Serves 4.

title: st. peters vegetables-russia(luk marinovannyi)
directions: Place drained onions back into the jar. Combine all other ingredients together in a saucepan. Bring to a boil
over medium heat. Pour over onions. Cap the jar tightly and allow to cool. Refrigerate for 2 weeks before serving.

title: easter egg candy
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Mix and add cherries, cut up and chopped nuts.
Add just a little cherry juice just for color. Roll into balls and set aside in refrigerator to chill while melting chocolate.
Add paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls and put on wax paper to cool.

title: zucchini  loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Combine zucchini, rice, wheat germ, 1 cup cheese, walnuts, mushrooms, green onions, eggs, oregano, garlic, thyme, sage, salt and pepper in a large bowl until well blended. Pour in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese. Bake for 50 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: west virginia hot dogs
directions: Fry hamburger and onions.
Add 1/2 cup water to keep from burning.
Add tomato soup, catsup and chili powder.
(This sauce also makes good spaghetti sauce.)

title: rice pilaf
directions: In large saucepan, bring chicken broth to boil; stir in rice, return to boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 15 to 20 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Meanwhile, cook mushrooms and onion in butter until tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and cool 1 minute more.
Add mushroom mixture to cooked rice and mix well. Serves 8.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and form into balls. In 9 x 13-inch pan, put balls. Mix 1 cup hot water with 1 beef bouillon cube dissolved in it. Pour over meat. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Turn meatballs over after 1/2 hour. Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes. Serves 3 to 4. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in mixing bowl. Combine egg, milk, corn and butter; stir into flour mixture.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into 1-inch hot shortening in skillet.
Fry for 4 to 5 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Makes 8 fritters.

title: candied carrots
directions: Heat butter and oil.
Add carrots and brown sugar.
Stir as if frying potatoes.
Takes about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cook to your taste, crunchy or soft, and lightly browned on edges.
Serves 2. This is as good as candied yams or sweet potatoes.

title: baked french cherry dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, milk, flour, granulated sugar and vanilla with hand beater.
Beat until smooth; spread cherries in greased oblong baking dish, 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch or square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Pour batter over cherries; bake, uncovered, until puffed and golden brown, 45 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: party dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with cauliflower, carrot sticks, bell pepper, celery, radishes and chips.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Salt and pepper one side.
Mix together margarine, parsley and a short squirt of lemon juice. Place 1/4 of mixture on each breast.
Roll like a cabbage roll. Roll chicken roll in flour.
(You can do this the night before.) Dip chicken in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry until brown, just about 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: fried corn
directions: Over a big bowl, cut kernels off ears of the corn, then gently scrape the back of a knife against cobs to extract milky liquid. Melt butter and bacon grease over medium heat in a large cast-iron skillet.
Stir in corn, stirring frequently.
Simmer until tender (8 to 10 minutes).
If corn seems to be drying out, add a bit of hot water to keep it moist.
Taste and season with sugar, salt and pepper to suit.
Makes 4 servings.

title: parmesan potato chips
directions: Lay potato chips in a single layer on a cookie sheet and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven until cheese is melted.

title: cleaette's sweet and sour brisket
directions: Dice onions and garlic.
Saute until lightly browned.
Sear brisket on both sides.
Combine all ingredients, except brisket, in a large casserole, mixing well.
Add brisket.
Cook, covered, 2 to 3 hours in a 350° oven.
Baste occasionally.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Make a paste of the bread, milk and butter.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add salmon, egg yolks and salt.
Mix well, then fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Bake in a greased pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift
the
dry	ingredients into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except
for the brown sugar and nuts;	beat for 3 minutes.
Pour
into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the brown
sugar and nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Good with Fruit Cocktail Cake Sauce poured over hot cake.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Mix popcorn and peanuts in large shallow roasting pan.
Cook sugar, corn syrup and margarine in heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium-heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, butter, vanilla, pumpkin and water. In another bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda. Slowly add dry ingredients into first bowl.
Then add nuts.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: aunt susie's yeast bread
directions: Sift flour and salt together in large mixing bowl.
Combine yeast and warm water.
Combine milk, sugar and shortening.
Add to flour mixture until soft dough is formed.
Knead dough and place in bowl with 1 tablespoon oil.
Cover and let rise until dough is approximately double in size.
Place on floured board and knead. Shape into small rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise again until double in size and bake at 350° until brown.

title: skillet orange-glazed pork chops
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook pork chops until they lose the pink color and are lightly browned on both sides.
Stir in orange marmalade, water and soy sauce; heat through.

title: breaded cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into buds.
Simmer in salted water until fork tender but not too soft.
Cool.
Dip buds in beaten egg seasoned with salt and pepper and then roll in bread crumbs to coat.
Fry in deep oil at 350° until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: supreme ham loaf
directions: Combine ham, onion powder, pork, eggs, salt, pepper and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into 9 x 5-inch baking dish.
Combine sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Mix well and spoon half over ham loaf.
Freeze other half of sauce for future use.

title: beefaroni pasta summer salad
directions: Saute green pepper, onions, celery and meat in margarine.
Add Beefaroni, cheese, peas and olives.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves six to eight.

title: cactus jelly
directions: Use underripe cactus, except for a few ripe ones to give color to the jelly.
Brush with vegetable brush under running cold water. Quarter and place in saucepan with enough water to cover.
Boil until very tender.
Mash with a potato masher and pour both liquid and pulp into a jelly bag to drip.
Measure juice and, for each two and one-half cups of juice add one (3 ounce) package of powdered pectin.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of lemon or lime juice and about one and a half times the volume of sugar as your measured juice.
Bring again to a full boil and keep boiling for 3 minutes, or until it tests done.
Pour into warm jars and cover tightly.
It is done when it drips 2 drips separately off of spoon.

title: jalapeno corn
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: spiced christmas punch
directions: Mix juices, water and brown sugar in a small pot.
Place spices in cheesecloth and tie with thread.
Drop into the juices and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and steep 5 minutes.
Remove spices and serve.

title: no-bake peanut butter treats
directions: Stir sugars and syrup together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening thoroughly.
Add peanut butter and cream together until smooth. Add sugar gradually.
Cream in well; add egg and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape dough into balls 1/2-inch thick.
Flatten with tines of fork.
Bake until done about 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; beat until well mixed.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour the berries over the top and again, do not stir.
Bake at 350° until crust rises to top and is golden brown.
You can use any fruit.

title: fried rice
directions: *Use as much shrimp, chicken and ham as you want for a Dutch oven full.

title: pineapple-cherry cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on bread.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken until tender with onion and celery leaves.
Cool and debone chicken.
Discard onion and celery leaves.
Place chicken in large casserole dish.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over top of chicken.
Let stand overnight.
(Will freeze well).
Cook, covered, 30 minutes at 350° and uncovered 15 minutes.
May serve out of dish or excellent if served in the Pepperidge Farm Puff Pastry Shells.

title: texas cole slaw
directions: Chop and mix together the cabbage, green pepper, onion and olives.
Bring to boil the remaining ingredients; cool.
Pour over chopped mixture; stir well.
Chill 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: eggplant caviar with tapenade
directions: Prick eggplant with fork and place on baking sheet.
Combine eggplant and next 8 ingredients.
Serve with Tapenade and French bread.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: swedish pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 275° about 30 minutes or until light brown in color.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again after cookies have cooled.

title: self-rising yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Add milk until well mixed.
Add the yeast mixture.
Roll out and cut into biscuits. Let rise in pan and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil water, sugar, shortening and raisins together about 3 minutes until sugar is well dissolved.
Put aside to cool.

title: olive creamed potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes.
Pour cream into skillet; add potatoes.
Heat slowly over medium heat until cream bubbles over potatoes.
Add onion and olives.
When potatoes are thoroughly heated, add salt and pepper.
Serve at once, garnished with paprika and parsley. Serves 6.

title: vegetable sandwich filling
directions: Mix well together.
Spread on your favorite sandwich bread.

title: sliced cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers (do not pare).
