Add other vegetables and salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Remove garlic cloves; drain well.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and heat to boiling point.
Can and seal.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease and flour a tube pan. Mix eggs, sugar, and oil; add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, milk, extract, and coconut. Pour into tube pan and bake 55 minutes. Cool in pan for 1 minute before removing. Pour sauce over hot cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until they are frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts, then beat in zucchini last.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans, 9 x 5-inch and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let loaves cool in pan for 10 minutes before inverting on rack.
Let cool completely.
Raisins may be added.
Remember add zucchini last.
Freezes well!

title: chili cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature.
Mix well.
Add nuts and garlic powder; mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chili powder. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill until firm.

title: homemade bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the water, salt, sugar and honey, then add the dry yeast on top of the mixture.
Let the yeast dissolve for about 10 minutes.
Then add the wheat germ, oat bran and bran flakes and stir in flour until the batter is thick. Pour into kneading pan or on the table.
Knead until stiff or about 15 minutes.
Grease top of dough; cover and let set until it rises to double in size, then divide into five loaves and leave to rise again.
Bake in 275° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: cucumber pickle
directions: Step 1:
Heat 1 gallon water to boiling point.
Add coarse salt.
Let set 7 days.

title: wacky cake frosting
directions: In
large
saucepan add all ingredients except vanilla. Stir over
a
low
heat until sugar dissolves.
Gradually increase heat to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, remove from heat and
add vanilla.
Set
pan in cold water and stir until thick pouring consistency.
Pour over cake and set aside until frosting resembles fudge.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute onion in drippings for five minutes.
Drain off grease. Add meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for at least 1 hour.
May even be cooked in a slow cooker if you have one.
Leave it on for about three or four hours.
Serve with onion rolls or over cooked noodles.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, milk, cornflakes, salt and pepper. Form into 6 patties, roll in flour and brown in fat.
Place in baking pan.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crescent canapes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften cream cheese and combine all ingredients except rolls.
Open rolls and divide into 4 rectangles.
Divide cream cheese mixture into fourths and spread on rectangles.
Roll up lengthwise and cut into 8 pieces.
Brush with beaten egg whites and sprinkle on poppy or sesame seed (optional).
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Makes 32 canapes.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Beat egg; add milk, salt and pepper.
Add shrimp; toss to coat all.
Dip shrimp in cracker crumbs and drop into hot, deep oil. Fry until brown.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, buttermilk and shortening.
Drop onto greased griddle.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix well and sprinkle 1/4 mixture in bottom of cake pan.
(Do not press.)

title: bubke
directions: Heat butter and milk.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and sour cream.
Add warm butter and milk.
(Put yeast in cup with a little warm water, sugar and flour.)
When yeast activates, add with butter and milk.
Leave until dough doubles in size.
Punch down and knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or round. Let sit until doubles again.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cut up fine the onion, pepper and celery.
Simmer in butter; brown slightly.
Fry hamburger with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cook together for a few hours.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: macaroni casserole(daddy's salad)
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Brown ground beef; add chopped onions.
Add kidney beans with juice. Add seasonings as desired.
Add tomatoes, cut up,
with juice. Combine.
Put in large casserole.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Add cheese a few minutes before removing from oven to melt.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Heat vinegar, celery seed, salt, mustard seed and sugar. Let cool. Pour over cabbage, green pepper, pimento and onion. Let stand overnight. Serves 10 to 12.

title: banana nog
directions: Process milk and bananas in blender until smooth.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Stir in milk mixture.
Heat to simmering over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Lightly beat egg yolks in small bowl; whisk about 1/2 cup milk mixture into egg yolks.
Whisk yolk mixture back into saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat, stir in rum, liqueur and vanilla.
Pour into large heatproof pitcher or bowl.
Cover; refrigerate until chilled.
Just before serving, stir half and half into eggnog mixture.
Serve in mugs.
Garnish with whipped cream and sprinkle of cocoa.
Tie pieces of ribbon around candy canes. Use as stirrers.

title: barbecued beef on a bun
directions: Heat oil.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Crumble meat and brown it.
Mix the catsup, mustard, vinegar, salt, pepper, paprika, cumin and chili powder in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over meat and mix together.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: fruit tea
directions: Let tea cool. Use gallon container. Pour pineapple juice into container; add lemon juice and sugar and mix well. Add boiled tea after it has cooled. Finish filling container with water.

title: milk punch
directions: Place in a large bowl; beat until frothy.
Pour into chilled punch bowl.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: egg-on-a-stick
directions: Note: Be careful with this one or you have a real mess.

title: chili tamale pie
directions: Lightly grease 13x9 baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain tamales, reserve liquid and discard fat.
Remove wrapping from tamales and line dish with tamales.
Stir together liquid from tamales and chili.	Pour over tamales.
Saute bell pepper and onions in small amount of oil.
Sprinkle peppers and onions on top of chili.
Bake approximately 20 minutes to heat through.
Remove and cover with cheese and tostitos.
Return to oven and bake approximately 12 minutes until cheese is melted.
Tabasco or red pepper can be added if desired.
Serve with tostitos or crackers. Serves 6-8.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Cream the sugar, flour and eggs.
Stir in the creamed corn. Put the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or any baking dish. Cover the mixture with milk (enough to cover the top).
Put slabs of butter on top of the milk.
Bake at 350° until thick on top, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix thoroughly until
batter
is smooth.
Melt 2 tablespoons oleo and mix in
batter.
Cook on hot griddle.
Makes 8 to 10 medium pancakes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Spread potatoes evenly over bottom of well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Break corned beef into fairly large pieces.
Spread over potatoes.
Combine soup and water; blend thoroughly and heat in saucepan over low heat to boiling point.
Stir constantly.
Pour over meat and potatoes. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Serve while piping hot.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, 1/4 cup of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture. Combine egg, applesauce, milk and oil in a small bowl.
Add applesauce mixture to dry mixture, stirring just until moistened. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: turkeyburger casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in large frying pan.
Add 3 1/2 to 4 cups of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cover with lid and simmer 15 minutes.

title: pickled slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onions and put in large glass jar.
Boil vinegar, turmeric, celery seed, salt and sugar and pour hot over cabbage and onions.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Serve on hot dogs or make reubens.
Use red cabbage if you like for color.

title: pasta frittata or spaghetti and eggs
directions: Leftover brown or white rice will also work.
Large pasta shells or ziti don't work well.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until emulsified. Store in refrigerator.

title: baby carrots and turnips
directions: Peel and cut turnips into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Steam carrots and turnips until crisp and tender, about 10 minutes. Drain well.

In a medium nonreactive saucepan, combine butter, lemon juice and cayenne pepper with carrots and turnips and cook, tossing over medium heat, until the butter has melted and vegetables are coated and warm, about 1 minute.
Season with salt to taste.
Serve warm.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add onion, peppers (cut into julienne strips) and saute about 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Add beef.

Sprinkle with garlic powder. Saute, stirring lightly, until browned. Add tomatoes and bouillon cube and simmer 10 minutes. Blend cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt. Stir into meat mixture and cook until thickened. Add onion and green peppers. Heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately with whipped potatoes or buttered rice.
Serves 6.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt and sugar and pour over kraut mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hominy scramble
directions: Fry bacon partially done (not crispy).
Remove from pan and cut in bite-size pieces.
Add green pepper to drippings.
When cooked, add hominy and heat through.
Add bacon.
Add hot sauce to eggs and beat slightly.
Add salt to taste.
Pour eggs in hominy mixture and continue to cook while stirring until eggs are set. Serves 4.

title: carrot cake icing
directions: Beat with mixer until well blended.

title: lazy pierogie(polish, lenine)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add milk if too heavy to roll.
Roll into 1-inch thick pieces and flatten.
Slice at angle to make 4-inch pieces.
Put into boiling water.
They are done when they float to top.
Serve with buttered, browned bread crumbs or butter sauteed onions.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all together, except shrimp, in mixer for 10 minutes at high speed.
Drain, rinse and break up shrimp.
Add to other ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: goldwater beans
directions: Cook beans until tender. Brown meat in bacon fat.
Add to beans and other ingredients. Cook until well blended.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine the cucumbers, onion, green pepper in a bowl.
Ad the sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Can be kept about 3 months.

title: smoked pork chops with polenta
directions: Pour broth into a shallow 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish. Gradually and smoothly stir in polenta; mix in corn.
Lay pork chops on top of polenta mixture. Bake in a 350° oven until pork chops are hot in thickest part, 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle meat with grated Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley. Serves 4.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar well. Press on sides and bottom of 9-inch spring pan. Place in freezer. Preheat oven to 450°. Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth and light. Beat in eggs, vanilla and cornstarch until blended. With spoon, stir in sour cream and pour into pan. Bake 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce heat to 200° and bake 45 minutes. Very quickly crack oven door and let stand 3 hours. Wrap in plastic wrap after removing sides of pan and chill.

title: smoked turkey and vegetable salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine turkey, potatoes, broccoli, squash, carrots, pepper and onion.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice, dill, parsley and garlic powder.
Fold mayonnaise mixture into turkey and vegetables mixture.
Cover and chill at least one hour.

title: dago spaghetti
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and make into meatballs.
Put cooking oil in a skillet and brown the meatballs.
Take them up and set aside.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the cheese, in a baking dish. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly.
Add cheese; bake for 15 more minutes.

title: cold oven pecan pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and milk, beating thoroughly. Add flavoring.

title: chili manicotti
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Stir in soup and water; heat thoroughly.
Cook manicotti shells in salted boiling water; drain.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, jalapenos and 1 cup of cheese; mix well.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in oil.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add onion and pepper; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Blend in cornstarch with a little water.
Add to mixture with soy sauce. Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; take off bone.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine broth and soup; bring to a boil and pour over chicken. Combine flour, buttermilk and margarine; spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Pour spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage or Ricotta cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine both ingredients and whip until smooth.
Store in air tight container.
Serve with fruit.
(If serving apples, they need to soak in water and lemon juice so they do not turn brown.)

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Cook roast until medium rare; slice thin.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Cook in Dutch oven for 1 hour over low heat.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble. Save 2 tablespoons of drippings. Cut or tear broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces (using stem is optional).
Cut onions, if used, into small pieces. Mix broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, sunflower seeds and onions, if used, together.

title: salad
directions: Put greens into mixing bowl. Add olives, almonds, and cheese. Pour dressing over mixture and stir.
Gently add oranges. Serve with croutons on top of salad or as a side. Yields
6 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread(given to clo fletcher by clara hollingsworth)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese dish
directions: Boil macaroni until tender with salt, drain macaroni and add cream, eggs and margarine, stir until margarine melts.
Cut up cheese into small pieces into macaroni; mix well.
Put macaroni and cheese into a medium size ovenware dish.
Bake about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and starts to turn brown.
Bake at 350°. Let cool and serve.
Serves 5.

title: blueberry-orange bread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water in small bowl.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice and 3 teaspoons orange rind.
Beat egg with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with orange liquid, beating until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart loaf pan or 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack and glaze while hot.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve jello flavors separately, using 1 cup boiling water for each.
Stir marshmallows into lemon flavor; set aside.
Add 3/4 cup cold water to lime. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill until set.
Add 3/4 cup cold water to raspberry; set aside at room temperature.
Add cream cheese to lemon mixture, beat until blended.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Then blend in mayonnaise, whipped cream and drained, crushed pineapple.
Chill until very thick and spoon gently over lime jello.
Chill until set, but not firm.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place 1/3 of mixed greens in large bowl. Dot with 2 tablespoons mayonnaise, 1/3 onion, 1/3 cup of cheese and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and a dash of salt and pepper. Repeat for 3 more layers. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix all seasonings and put into a shaker.
Makes about 1 cup. Keep shaker covered in a cool, dry place.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop up broccoli and onion together.
Add grated cheese and crumbled bacon.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise; pour over broccoli mixture and let set 2 hours before eating.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thickens; boil 1 minute.
Remove, carefully stir in egg.
Blend in butter, vanilla and coconut. Cool; stir constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Top with meringue with toasted coconut.

title: easy pizza
directions: Combine the first 4
ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add oil and water and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour and mix well.
Turn
out on a floured board and knead
until
smooth.
Oil a 2 quart mixing bowl and place dough in	it,
turning
it
once to give a light cover of oil. Cover with
a
cloth and put in a warm place to rise to double its size (consult
the package).
In Florida this is no problem, even the porch is warm enough.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grind vegetables and strain.
Press out all juice.
Mix with nuts.
Mix with cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Will spread 1 loaf bread.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for days.

title: brazo mercedes(filipino dessert)
directions: Combine egg yolks and condensed milk.
Cook on top of a double boiler until thick or of spreading consistency.
Add the butter and vanilla and mix well.
Set aside.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sprinkle with coconut if desired.
Do not freeze.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; mix with cheese.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add to pineapple and cheese.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs, mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well the first six ingredients.
Then add the next six. Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rho rho's rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 3 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt. Stir together eggs, water and oil; add to flour mixture.
Beat with mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat with mixer for 3 minutes on high.
Using a spoon, stir in rest of flour.
Put in a large bowl and refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.
Stir dough down and let rest for 10 minutes.
Shape rolls and let rise for 40 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: oma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
(You may use white sugar, cinnamon sugar, red or green sugar crystals, etc.).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: amalene tucker's clouds at sunrise
directions: Beat egg whites until frosty; add or beat in cream of tarter, then gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in crushed crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a well buttered 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack. Spread Cool Whip over top and spoon on pie filling.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: crab spread
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery; add peppers and crabmeat. Cook, stir-fry style, until mixture begins to brown.
Add cilantro and salt; cook a bit more until well mixed.
Serve with tortillas or crackers.

title: pearl barnes' and the late vera mckinney's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let cool.
Cream together good sugar, brown sugar, shortening and salt.
Add eggs.
Mix together cinnamon, soda and flour; blend and then add oatmeal mixture.
Beat so it's incorporated.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two 8-inch pans.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring first four ingredients together and boil, 4-8 minutes. Mix in the marshmallow, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8 inch buttered dish and cool.

title: macaroon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of coconut into dish.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in tight container and use as needed.
Mix with hot water, 3 teaspoons per cup or to taste.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 4 round cake pans. Blend all ingredients together except egg whites.
Fold in egg whites last.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: green tomato sweet relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, peppers, onions and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour. Drain well.
Add the remaining ingredients; tie spices in cloth. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: pineapple bread casserole
directions: Combine sugar and butter, beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pineapple.
Fold in cubed bread.
Turn into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: croquettes
directions: Mix meat, cream sauce, onion and parsley.
Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Chill until stiff.
Cut into squares or oblong.
Coat with flour; roll in egg/water mixture, then in crumbs.
Allow to dry.
Fry in deep fat (375°) until brown, about 3 minutes or panfry in about 1/2 cup hot fat over medium heat.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: eggnog cake
directions: In order given, measure ingredients into large mixer bowl. Blend 1/2 minute at low speed and 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan immediately.
Serve with Fruit Sauce (recipe follows).

title: eddie's pecan cookies
directions: Cream everything except flour and nuts, then add them.
Make a ball of dough.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Pinch off small pieces and roll into balls.
Pat down on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, until light brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: rich vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 4-quart freezer and turn until freezer turns hard.
Top with favorite topping and serve.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry; remove skin if desired.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken in butter mixture to coat both sides. Arrange, meaty side up, in a single layer in same pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and richly glazed. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cucumber dill slice
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water. Measure 1/4 cup gelatin.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Prepare cucumber slices using a food processor with 1 mm slicing blade. Cut in half.
Arrange overlapping slices in gelatin.
Chill until set but not firm (5 minutes).
Chill remaining gelatin until thickened (50 minutes).
Chop seeded cucumbers.
Fold in cucumber, onion, and dill.
Spoon into mold.
Chill until firm (4 hours). Unmold.
Makes 12 servings.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Blend together sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternately add flour and whipping cream, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti almost tender; drain.
Cook ground beef and onion and drain.
Mix ground beef with 1/2 jar of Ragu sauce, egg, 1/2 package Mozzarella, Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well. Add ziti and toss gently to coat.

title: weight watchers cheese melts
directions: Spread muffins with avocado, ham and cheese.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes.
(1 F, 2 proteins and 2 breads.)

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Let stand 1 hour.
Pour over slaw.
Pour into containers and freeze.

title: oyster cracker nips
directions: Mix oil and seasonings together.
Pour over crackers and toss until all are coated.
Place in airtight container; let set at least one hour before serving.
Will keep for several weeks; keep covered.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Baste liberally every time you turn pork chops.

title: kahlua under the kitchen sink
directions: Simmer water and sugar for 25 minutes until clear.
Cool completely.
Add coffee, vanilla and vodka.
Put mixture into a jug and place it under the kitchen sink.
Shake it once each day when you do the dishes.
(Don't sneak!) After 3 weeks, strain through a paper towel and pour into bottles or jars.
Great for Christmas gifts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven 350.
Drain liquid from corn and reserve 1/4 cup. Add milk to measure 1 C liquid.
Set aside.
In saucepan, heat butter, add flour, salt & pepper (it will be a paste).
Slowly add liquid (blend well) to create a thin gravy.
Cook and stir constantly until thickened-remove from heat.
Add drained corn and slowly add beaten eggs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350, 45-50 min.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes at high speed.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan
or 2 small loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate swirl sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour 3 times each.
Mix butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Beat until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time and continue to mix.
Gradually add flour and dairy sour cream to mixture.
Add vanilla and pineapple flavoring and mix.
Place 2 cups of mixture in a small bowl, then add the baking chocolate, food coloring and mace; stir well.
Line a 10-inch tube pan with waxed paper.
Grease with butter.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour half of batter into pan, then spoon in the chocolate batter alternately.
Use fork to twirl the batter.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
(One hour at 325° and the last 30 minutes turn oven to 350°.)

title: baked cheese cakes
directions: Cream together cream cheese, eggs, vanilla, sugar and bake at 350 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: strawberry crush
directions: In food processor with knife blade attached, blend strawberries until they resemble finely shaved ice, stopping occasionally to scrape sides.
Add yogurt and sugar and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Mix and press pretzels and butter into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together, then add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel mixture. Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Add frozen raspberries and let gel.
Spread over cream cheese mixture and chill until set.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Combine cheese, butter and salt in food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Add flour and pecans and process until blended. Form dough into teaspoon-sized balls and place on greased baking sheets.
Flatten with a fork, dipping fork in flour if necessary to keep from sticking.
Sprinkle crackers with cayenne.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes, until just beginning to brown.
Serve hot or cool to room temperature.
Servings:
12 (serving size = 2 or 3 crackers).
Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: beef and salad stir-fry
directions: Thin-slice beef and cook 2 to 3 minutes in wok.

title: cool whip cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
Remove from oven when done. Punch holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Add Cool Whip.
Crush up candy bars and put on top of Cool Whip.

title: chunky garden salad
directions: Cut into large chunks the tomatoes, cucumbers and onion.
Dice the jalapenos.
Mix together in a large bowl. Cover with your favorite Italian dressing and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: In a large bowl, measure the first 7 ingredients and mix with a fork.
Make a hole in the center of mixture and add the pumpkin, sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix well with an electric mixer, then add the vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips or raisins and nuts (if used).
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lizzie cake
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes and cool. Then add eggs and mix well.
Sift together the following and add to mixture:
flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add walnuts, dates or candied fruit.
Beat all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger-cabbage casserole
directions: Place a generous layer of sliced cabbage in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add rice and seasonings and mix well.
Alternately layer meat mixture and cabbage, ending with cabbage.
Mix soup and water and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (or until cabbage cooks).

title: hash brown egg bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine hash browns, bacon, 1/2 cup cheese and salt.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In bowl, beat eggs and milk until smooth; pour over hash brown mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden.
Top with remaining cheese.
Yield 8 servings.

title: quick sauteed beef tenderloin slices
directions: All items found within the heart and home, half cup of friendship and a cup of thoughtfulness.
Cream together with a pinch of powdered tenderness, very lightly beaten.
In a bowl of loyalty, with a cup of faith, and one of hope and one of charity. Be sure to add a spoonful each of happiness that sings and also the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with the sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good-natured pan and serve repeatedly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse. In a large bowl, mix drained spaghetti, chicken, pimentos, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper. Add soup, broth and half of cheese. Put into casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam or buttered. Top with rest of cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown the beef.
Add other ingredients, except beans, cooking oil and flour; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
In a small bowl, mix oil and flour together until smooth; add undrained kidney beans. Add mixture to kettle.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix together 3 eggs and 1/2 cup milk.
Add squash, onion, salt and pepper, cheese and crackers.
Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Stir all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Saute onion, broccoli and mushrooms in oleo.
Mix soup with milk.
Combine everything and put in greased pan.
Grate 2 ounces Cheddar cheese on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: butter pecan heath bar cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Make cake as directed.
Cool halfway. Using a fork, poke holes all over the top of the cake in the pan. Drizzle Eagle Brand on top of cake allowing it to go into holes. Refrigerate.
When cake is chilled, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Refrigerate.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate three days, stirring three or four times a day.
Put in containers and freeze. Leave a 1-inch space in container.

title: beef roast and gravy
directions: Put oil in pan.
Heat on high until oil is hot.
Brown roast on each side; turn heat down to 300°.
Put 1 cup water in pan, add soup and put lid on or foil over.
Cook until meat is tender. Takes about 2 hours or more.
Makes its own gravy.
Can cook in oven or on top of stove.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole dish, place crushed potato chips to cover bottom of dish.
Put a layer of asparagus, eggs and cheese; repeat for second layer.
Combine small amount of asparagus juice with mushroom soup; pour over top of layers.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Put chicken breasts in crock-pot; add spaghetti sauce and garlic powder.
Let cook all day and serve with noodles and a salad.

title: two bean fritters
directions: Cook beans in salt water just until tender.
Drain well or use canned beans.
Heat 2 to 3 inch cooking oil to 375°.
Combine egg and milk.
Add flour.
Add beans, stirring just until moistened. Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry several at a time until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: german potato salad
directions: To bacon fat, add 1 rounded tablespoon flour, 2/3 cup cider vinegar, 2/3 cup water and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bring to a boil; cool a bit before pouring over the potatoes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chopped cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
Mix well. Chill.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese and seasoning.
Dip chicken pieces into oil or melted margarine, then into crumb mixture.
Place on foil-lined cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Turn each piece over and bake approximately 10 more minutes.
Serve with favorite dips such as sweet and sour, duck sauce or barbecue.

title: snow peas and mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
Stir in snow peas and soy sauce.
Cook until crisp-tender.
Toss and serve.
Serves 4.

title: parmesan sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over fettucini.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Make into long rolls, and place on waxed paper.
Freeze, slice, and bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes.

title: simply super tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomatoes in serving dish.
In small bowl or jar with tight-fitting lid, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour dressing over tomato slices.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: effortless no fail desserts
directions: Lift handset (located on the telephone).

title: cheese straws whole wheat
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salt, in food processor (2 batches) or by hand.
Process until mixture comes together in a ball.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough, about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips or rounds.
Bake on ungreased baking sheets for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with salt while still hot.
Serve hot with cocktails or cold with soups.

title: vegetable jello
directions: Mix all together.
Use pineapple juice together with cold water to make 2 cups liquid total.
Put in 8 3/4 x 12-inch long pan.
Makes 15 servings.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine, one egg and pecans.
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drain pineapple and spread evenly over cake mixture.
Mix cream cheese, two eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut in small squares; is very rich.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done in 2 or 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Frost when cooled with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate raspberry crumb bars
directions: Heat oleo in mixing bowl. Add sugar and salt. Stir in flour with mixer running. Mix well. Put 1 3/4 cups of mix into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish; press level with floured fingers. Bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes, until edge browns. Heat 1 cup of split morsels with Eagle Brand; heat and stir until smooth. Spread over hot crust. Stir chopped nuts and raspberry jam together and pour over chocolate. Smooth and cover with remainder of morsels. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 36 bars.

title: springtime cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish and salt well.
Top each pork chop with a lemon slice and an onion slice.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour 1 tablespoon catsup over each chop.
Add a little water to the baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: In a large pot, place the first 10 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then reduce to medium heat.
Mix together hamburger, egg, garlic powder and rice.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix well and stuff peppers with meat.
Trim the bits of pepper from cut-off tops and add to pot.
Place stuffed peppers in pot and cook on medium-low heat for 2 hours.
Remainder of meat mixture is rolled into large meatballs and added to pot as well.
Mix room-temperature sour cream and flour well to remove lumps.
Slowly add about 1 1/2 cups of stock from pot to sour cream mix, blending well.
Add sour cream mixture to soup pot and simmer (do not boil) for 10 to 15 minutes.
Adjust seasonings to taste and serve over additional cooked rice.
Nonfat sour cream may be used as well.
An old cherished family recipe.

title: easy homemade cheesecake
directions: Add cornstarch to yogurt.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Add yogurt and mix.
Add vanilla and blend.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until edge just begins to brown.
Turn oven off.
Open door several inches.
Leave in oven 1 to 3 hours.
Store in refrigerator.
May serve with fruit of choice.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Cook pork chops over medium heat until brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top each chop with green pepper ring.
Fill each ring with 1 tablespoon rice.
Carefully pour 1/4 cup stewed tomatoes on rice in each ring.
Pour remaining tomatoes into skillet.
Cover tightly; simmer 1 hour or until done.
Add small amount of water if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: basic biscuits
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
With a pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture; add milk all at once.
Stir with a fork just until the dough clings together.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead gently for 10 to 12 strokes.
Pat or roll the dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut dough with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, dipping cutter into flour between cuts.
Transfer biscuits to an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix nuts, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix pineapple with pudding.
Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill overnight.
